char_102_texas_CN_001.voiceText: My next mission is to protect you, Doctor.

char_102_texas_CN_002.voiceText: I don't say much? That's because I'd rather avoid thinking about most things.

char_102_texas_CN_003.voiceText: Our job is to handle life and death.

char_102_texas_CN_004.voiceText: I usually listen to Sora's songs when I'm driving.

char_102_texas_CN_005.voiceText: Cigarette? Oh, no, this is chocolate. You've gotta replenish your energy regularly. Which reminds me... do you want some coffee?

char_102_texas_CN_006.voiceText: How long have I worked for Penguin Logistics? When did I start... I've forgotten how long it's been...

char_102_texas_CN_007.voiceText: Be aware of the Red Wolf. She's not evil, but... she's not like us.

char_102_texas_CN_008.voiceText: No matter how hard I run, my past will catch me one day.

char_102_texas_CN_009.voiceText: My independent lifestyle and rowdy friends have brought me a lot of trouble... but I kind of like it this way.

char_102_texas_CN_010.voiceText: Is it time for a break?

char_102_texas_CN_011.voiceText: Code name Texas. My duties consist of vehicle driving, cargo transportation and personnel safety. Keep mission briefings as simple as possible, please.

char_102_texas_CN_018.voiceText: I'm not good at ordering others.

char_102_texas_CN_031.voiceText: A few of them passed through.

char_102_texas_CN_032.voiceText: I may have underestimated this operation's difficulty...

char_102_texas_CN_033.voiceText: Do you have the materials I need? It'd save me a lot of trouble.

char_500_noirc_CN_001.voiceText: What's up, Doctor? Me, I'm just on standby.

char_500_noirc_CN_002.voiceText: My shield? Fun fact: I personally provide a portion of the energy it needs.

char_500_noirc_CN_003.voiceText: What I look like beneath the mask? Well, I... Actually, let's keep it secret for a bit longer.

char_500_noirc_CN_004.voiceText: Man, nothing better than a break after you finish a mission.

char_500_noirc_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, if I get to know you better, I figure my shield's gonna get even sturdier.

char_500_noirc_CN_008.voiceText: Course I know where my limit's at. But I don't wanna make Yato worry about me, which is what matters. We'll worry about the rest some other time!

char_500_noirc_CN_009.voiceText: There's always the need for guys like me, you know? Nah, I'm not trying to act high and mighty. What I'm saying is: when you have a VIP plus a lot of danger, you need a guy to stand between them, that's all.

char_500_noirc_CN_010.voiceText: Sometimes you've just gotta take off the mask and catch a breather.

char_500_noirc_CN_011.voiceText: Defender Noir Corne, reporting for duty. You need VIP protection, I'm your guy.

char_500_noirc_CN_012.voiceText: Cool... So this stuff is what Grandpa Rangers was talking about earlier.

char_500_noirc_CN_019.voiceText: Holding the frontline is a Defender's most important job!

char_500_noirc_CN_029.voiceText: Even guys like me are happy to get through tough battles like these.

char_500_noirc_CN_032.voiceText: This wouldn't have happened if I'd worn my good mask! God dammit!

char_500_noirc_CN_036.voiceText: You wanna get some drinks after work?

char_503_rang_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, I greatly admire your genius. It's my honor to be your guard.

char_503_rang_CN_002.voiceText: Based on my prior experience, I can say you will surely be a great leader one day, Doctor.

char_503_rang_CN_003.voiceText: I have an unusual skin tone, you say? It came from back when I snuck into a biolab, and... Please, I'm joking around.

char_503_rang_CN_004.voiceText: I need to have this scarf on even when I sleep, or else my neck will get cold.

char_503_rang_CN_007.voiceText: My appearance may be too exotic for the people in some remote towns. It's unavoidable I'd draw attention from curious onlookers.

char_503_rang_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, I'm surprised by your care for me! There are very few besides Durin who ask me how well I am.

char_503_rang_CN_009.voiceText: When I go barefoot, I can sense where enemies are based on the vibrations sent through the ground.

char_503_rang_CN_010.voiceText: Hmm... Snoring is a bad habit. The other rangers will hear you.

char_503_rang_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Rangers, the Sniper. Call whenever you need me.

char_503_rang_CN_029.voiceText: Challenge after challenge. Exactly what we wanted, right, Noir Corne?

char_503_rang_CN_031.voiceText: A few of them got through. We merely did okay.

char_503_rang_CN_032.voiceText: Oh no, I'm out of breath...

char_503_rang_CN_033.voiceText: If you need anything of me, just say the word.

char_503_rang_CN_034.voiceText: Urgh! Please, leave my tail be...

char_503_rang_CN_036.voiceText: You have peculiar taste if you're this fond of me!

char_503_rang_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, how can I help you?

char_501_durin_CN_001.voiceText: Morning, Doctor... Mind if I just leave my sleeping bag here...? Thanks. The rest is up to you...

char_501_durin_CN_002.voiceText: How do I fight? Using Arts, of course... Want me to show you the power of earth?

char_501_durin_CN_003.voiceText: What time is it...? You see, I don't work mornings, noons, afternoons, or nights...

char_501_durin_CN_004.voiceText: You'll make an S-sized uniform for me...? No thanks. My oversized one works as a sheet when I take naps... plus, it's really warm.

char_501_durin_CN_007.voiceText: Dooooctoooooor? I'd like to sleep. I got an invitation to the Speedy Sleep Contest, you see.

char_501_durin_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, check this out. This isn't my regular staff, it's a pendulum. You're feeling very sleepy and will nap in 5 minutes without giving me any assignments... Zzzz...

char_501_durin_CN_009.voiceText: I was hoping I could tell you about my hometown, Doctor.

char_501_durin_CN_010.voiceText: After you went to sleep, I somehow didn't feel sleepy at all anymore... Hmmmph...

char_501_durin_CN_011.voiceText: Hello? Hellooooo? Can you hear me? Down here. Down heeeeere! Nice meeting you, big Doctor. I'm the Caster Durin.

char_501_durin_CN_017.voiceText: The secret to staying healthy is to sleep whenever you can.

char_501_durin_CN_018.voiceText: Captain's orders: everyone, save your energy and take a nap!

char_501_durin_CN_019.voiceText: I wanna dig a hole in the ground and make a shelter to sleep in, if you don't mind.

char_501_durin_CN_023.voiceText: What a pain in the A.

char_501_durin_CN_029.voiceText: Why do we have to take on annoying missions like this? Can't we do something easier... Still, it's nice that we won.

char_501_durin_CN_030.voiceText: Of course we won. I worked real hard supporting you with my Arts, after all.

char_501_durin_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, are you still worried about those enemies that got through?

char_501_durin_CN_032.voiceText: Ugghh... Sorry... I'll try harder next time...

char_501_durin_CN_033.voiceText: The Land of Giants... Here I aaaaaaaaaaaaaaam!

char_501_durin_CN_036.voiceText: I'm in a good mood, so how about a magic trick?

char_502_nblade_CN_001.voiceText: Hey, Doctor. Do me a favor and just tell me what you need done.

char_502_nblade_CN_002.voiceText: I'll be watching you even after work today.

char_502_nblade_CN_004.voiceText: My skin is quite sensitive to sunlight, so whenever possible, please assign me to nighttime missions instead.

char_502_nblade_CN_007.voiceText: There's limits to what I'm capable of, but even so, I want to help ease the burden you carry, Doctor.

char_502_nblade_CN_008.voiceText: I can't help but feel envious when I see how the other Operators fight...

char_502_nblade_CN_009.voiceText: I need no particular reason to fight for you, Doctor. I hope that one day we can have a lively battle on the front lines...

char_502_nblade_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, let me be your guardian, now and forever...

char_502_nblade_CN_011.voiceText: Vanguard Yato here. Are you the one for me to protect?

char_502_nblade_CN_018.voiceText: All teammates will follow your tactics, Doctor.

char_502_nblade_CN_020.voiceText: Targets spotted. Get ready for battle.

char_502_nblade_CN_029.voiceText: As long as we follow the Doctor's orders, we won't have any problems.

char_502_nblade_CN_030.voiceText: The Doctor's brilliant command was the key to victory.

char_502_nblade_CN_031.voiceText: Victory is the most welcome news.

char_502_nblade_CN_032.voiceText: I apologize... We failed to execute your plan, Doctor...

char_502_nblade_CN_033.voiceText: Please send me to somewhere that sunlight can never touch.

char_502_nblade_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, thank you for always taking care of us.

char_502_nblade_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, I will be your shield.

char_122_beagle_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, I'm your guard for the day! Don't worry, I won't let any sketchy people get close to you! Just relax!

char_122_beagle_CN_002.voiceText: My training score for today...? Um, well, don't worry about it...

char_122_beagle_CN_003.voiceText: I can't shake the anxiety I have before battle, and that makes Captain Fang really nervous too... What should I do? Doctor!

char_122_beagle_CN_004.voiceText: Hibiscus and Lava always complain to me about each other, but both of them are my good friends, and neither of them are wrong... Doctor, what should I do...?

char_122_beagle_CN_005.voiceText: Instructor Dobermann always told us, 'Even when after you finish your training, your number one goal on the battlefield is to stay alive.' Urgh... How can I become as strong and awesome as she is?

char_122_beagle_CN_007.voiceText: I'm still a rookie Operator, but I'm working hard! Hehehe, if you agree, I'd really love a compliment or two...

char_122_beagle_CN_008.voiceText: My Oripathy? It doesn't bother me all that much, I'm used to it. I just want to be with the people I care about until my disease has been cured... Ughh...

char_122_beagle_CN_009.voiceText: I didn't have much confidence before I came here, but I'm so glad now that I can protect you and everyone here! It's my dream to protect everyone! I really wish days like these could last forever.

char_122_beagle_CN_010.voiceText: Maybe it's time to have a little fun and doodle on the Doctor's face...

char_122_beagle_CN_011.voiceText: My codename is Beagle! I know I didn't do very well on my assessment, but I'll still do my best at my internship!

char_122_beagle_CN_012.voiceText: I did it! I've become stronger!

char_122_beagle_CN_013.voiceText: Finally, FINALLY! Now nobody's going to call me 'the Rookiest Rookie in the Rookieverse' anymore!

char_122_beagle_CN_018.voiceText: Huh? I am the captain? I don't feel right about Fang not being the captain...

char_122_beagle_CN_029.voiceText: It's my duty to protect everyone! My resolve will never falter, no matter the odds!

char_122_beagle_CN_030.voiceText: All enemies have been defeated! Rhodes Island Operators, you are the best!

char_122_beagle_CN_031.voiceText: Hooray, we won! Although a few enemies managed to get away... Ehehe...

char_122_beagle_CN_033.voiceText: What can I do for you?

char_122_beagle_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, can I come to your place to study every day?

char_123_fang_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, is there anything I can help you with?

char_123_fang_CN_002.voiceText: Thank you for believing in me! I'll keep up my work!

char_123_fang_CN_003.voiceText: Hibiscus and Lava are fighting again... What a pain. Why are they like this when they're siblings?

char_123_fang_CN_004.voiceText: We often have mock battles with Instructor Dobermann, but I always fail to grasp her skill. Doctor, next time you and Amiya observe our training, would you please give us some guidance?

char_123_fang_CN_005.voiceText: Is there something you want to tell me? Ah, I understand now. Someone on my team is late again, aren't they? I'll see to it that gets fixed.

char_123_fang_CN_007.voiceText: Lava and I are both Infected, but I didn't receive powerful Arts from it like she did...

char_123_fang_CN_008.voiceText: Rhodes Island is our home and shelter, Doctor. I will protect everyone here with my life.

char_123_fang_CN_009.voiceText: The ever-honest and reliable Beagle, the perceptive Kroos, the resourceful Lava and the energetic Hibiscus. I like everyone in this team... as long as Hibiscus doesn't force her newly invented dishes on me.

char_123_fang_CN_010.voiceText: Shhh! The Doctor's resting. We can talk outside.

char_123_fang_CN_011.voiceText: This is lancer Fang, the captain of Reserve Op Team A1. My team and I will do our best to serve Rhodes Island.

char_123_fang_CN_013.voiceText: I'm greatly honored by the promotion!

char_123_fang_CN_018.voiceText: I know well what a captain's duty is. Rest easy.

char_123_fang_CN_019.voiceText: Team, check your gear before departing.

char_123_fang_CN_029.voiceText: With the right plan, even Starters like us can win a tough fight!

char_123_fang_CN_030.voiceText: We have accomplished our objective as planned.

char_123_fang_CN_031.voiceText: We can't call a mission complete if we let even one enemy get away. Beagle, let's do better on the next one.

char_123_fang_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry for having failed you, Instructor Dobermann...

char_123_fang_CN_033.voiceText: Yes. I'm back. Is Kroos here too?

char_123_fang_CN_042.voiceText: I'm ready whenever you need me, Doctor.

char_124_kroos_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, it's such a nice day, so can't we take a little nap?

char_124_kroos_CN_002.voiceText: Hmm...? We're about to leave? But I just got up... Wait, is this the Doctor's office? How'd I get here?

char_124_kroos_CN_003.voiceText: Why am I always squinting? Because I don't want anyone to see my eyes. Nope, nobody~

char_124_kroos_CN_004.voiceText: I'm really careless and get hurt a lot... But Hibiscus heals me every time, so I'm not afraid of getting injured. Oh gosh, that 'Curing Cuisine' of hers though, I'm terrified of it...

char_124_kroos_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor! Someone left 10 alarm clocks by my bed! Who would do something so awful?!

char_124_kroos_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, let's play a game~ Put an apple on your head and we'll start~

char_124_kroos_CN_008.voiceText: I'm always looking for fun things to do as a way to ease the pain of my Oripathy, I guess. Plus, I love seeing other people smile~

char_124_kroos_CN_009.voiceText: One day, our journey with Rhodes Island will come to an end, and hopefully we'll all get to have a warm, neverending dream, lying in the sunshine~ That's my number one dream~

char_124_kroos_CN_010.voiceText: Can't believe the Doctor's a heavier sleeper than me...

char_124_kroos_CN_011.voiceText: Hi-hiii~ I'm Kroos~ I might be inexperienced, but I'll do the best I can~

char_124_kroos_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion~ What a lovely dream~ Huh? I'm not dreaming?

char_124_kroos_CN_018.voiceText: Huhhh~? Fang would make a better captain than me!

char_124_kroos_CN_019.voiceText: Listen, everyone~! Go on and take a break!

char_124_kroos_CN_020.voiceText: Why can't everyone try to get along...?

char_124_kroos_CN_024.voiceText: I won't sleep on the job~

char_124_kroos_CN_031.voiceText: Hmm, I guess this was a bit of a letdown...

char_124_kroos_CN_032.voiceText: S-sorry... I'll fight harder next time...!

char_124_kroos_CN_033.voiceText: Can I get my beauty sleep in here?

char_121_lava_CN_001.voiceText: Need something? If you don't... Oh, I know... I can tell you your fortune.

char_121_lava_CN_002.voiceText: Just tell me when there's work to do. But don't ever put her and me on the same team. I hate her guts. And don't get me started on the weird food she makes me eat... Just thinking about it makes me... euurghh...

char_121_lava_CN_003.voiceText: No one told me Hibiscus was here too before I came to Rhodes Island... It's too late for me to quit now...

char_121_lava_CN_004.voiceText: When on the battlefield, you've gotta act like it. I bet those people brought up in greenhouses have never thought about how you're supposed to aggravate or defeat the enemy. Ain't that right, Doctor?

char_121_lava_CN_005.voiceText: Have you heard that saying 'little sisters are righteous'? If it's true, then my sister is evil by default... at least she is as far as I'm concerned.

char_121_lava_CN_007.voiceText: Any instruments? I can sort of play the piano. My teacher in Leithanien said learning an instrument can improve your Arts affinity. It apparently also eases the impact that Oripathy has on your mind...

char_121_lava_CN_008.voiceText: I'm starving... Huh, what's this? You keep candy in here? Nom... I'm in the middle of my training, so should I really be eating this...

char_121_lava_CN_009.voiceText: Like, I don't have a big beef with Hibiscus... It's all water under the bridge. I'm fine with her as long as she doesn't force me to eat her medicine and food. After all, she was the one... who saved my life...

char_121_lava_CN_010.voiceText: I almost envy your ability to sleep like a log...

char_121_lava_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Lava. I'm a Caster. I'm just here cause I'm bored and want something to do... I've heard my sworn nemesis is here too, though... Can I just quit now?

char_121_lava_CN_013.voiceText: Did you forget? I don't need a cause to work for, and I don't need a team... but... thanks, I guess...

char_121_lava_CN_017.voiceText: As far as teamwork's concerned... I don't mind, as long as nobody messes up.

char_121_lava_CN_018.voiceText: I'm not good at this sort of stuff, but if you insist...

char_121_lava_CN_019.voiceText: Let's go. Keep an eye on my back.

char_121_lava_CN_020.voiceText: I can see their souls. They're mine to reap.

char_121_lava_CN_026.voiceText: Even the dead can't save you.

char_121_lava_CN_029.voiceText: The supreme form of arts? Huh, sounds interesting.

char_121_lava_CN_030.voiceText: I foresaw this result earlier. A perfect victory.

char_121_lava_CN_031.voiceText: My fortune telling isn't always right. Sometimes there's a lot of external noise and the outcome ends up different.

char_121_lava_CN_032.voiceText: Dammit... These evil spirits are too strong...

char_121_lava_CN_033.voiceText: Well, all right. I like working alone anyhow.

char_121_lava_CN_036.voiceText: Y-you're not gonna score points with me by doing that!

char_120_hibisc_CN_001.voiceText: Are you calling for me, Doctor? I feel so happy when we're together!

char_120_hibisc_CN_002.voiceText: Doctor! Dr. Kal'tsit said that you need to look after your physical wellbeing. In two words, E-A-T L-E-S-S! That's it.

char_120_hibisc_CN_003.voiceText: Hey, Doctor, do tell me if my sister starts acting all bossy with you! She needs my treatment!

char_120_hibisc_CN_004.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit teaches me tons of practical stuff, although it's tough to actually learn! I've at least always had a knack for nutrition, so I think I'm doing well at that!

char_120_hibisc_CN_005.voiceText: I feel more assured about everyone here compared with when I just joined Rhodes Island! And everyone eats my health food on schedule! But... why are their expressions all so weird after finishing eating?

char_120_hibisc_CN_007.voiceText: Tadaaaaaah! A special healthy meal just for you, Doctor! Uncaffeinated coffee and a hamburger without meat, cheese, pickles, or lettuce! Oh, and a salad comprised of 12 different vegetables!

char_120_hibisc_CN_008.voiceText: Say, Doctor, where does your family live? Are they well? I know there are things you can't talk to them about precisely because they're your family, but I think it doesn't hurt to at least try.

char_120_hibisc_CN_009.voiceText: Isn't it lonely to cook all by yourself? Let me help you out! Oh yeah, let's get Lava in here too!

char_120_hibisc_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, have you fallen asleep? Have a rest then. You need to sleep a lot to stay healthy.

char_120_hibisc_CN_011.voiceText: This is intern Hibiscus. From now on, I'll be in charge of the health management of you and every Operator at Rhodes Island. Thank you for your cooperation!

char_120_hibisc_CN_012.voiceText: Oh, I see! So that's how you do it!

char_120_hibisc_CN_013.voiceText: It's my honor to be promoted! Doctor, please supervise my work of health management!

char_120_hibisc_CN_017.voiceText: I won't fail you! Let me protect everyone!

char_120_hibisc_CN_018.voiceText: Acknowledged! I'll take good care of everyone! First, I need to get my special sustained-release medicine ready...

char_120_hibisc_CN_019.voiceText: Please take good care of yourself while I'm gone!

char_120_hibisc_CN_026.voiceText: I can heal your wound in no time!

char_120_hibisc_CN_029.voiceText: Even if everyone gets wounded, I can heal them all with my staff!

char_120_hibisc_CN_030.voiceText: My greatest motivation comes from everyone's health.

char_120_hibisc_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, would you like to have a taste of my new vitamin beverage?

char_120_hibisc_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor! Would you mind tasting this?

char_208_melan_CN_001.voiceText: H-hello, Doctor... It's good meeting you...

char_208_melan_CN_002.voiceText: Um... Sorry... I'm not a good talker...

char_208_melan_CN_003.voiceText: Yes... My parents are from Victoria. They used to do business there, but I haven't been able to contact them for a long time... I picked this code name because it reminds me of my home...

char_208_melan_CN_004.voiceText: Th-that masked Operator... makes me feel... nervous...

char_208_melan_CN_005.voiceText: It's not that... I'm trying to avoid others, it's just, I'm not sure... how I should act...

char_208_melan_CN_007.voiceText: Sorry to make you worry again, Ansel... But you don't have to give me special treatment. Many more people need your help.

char_208_melan_CN_008.voiceText: Oripathy granted me powerful senses, but they are going away... But I will not flinch... There's so much more I want to talk about with everyone...

char_208_melan_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, could you accept this bottle of perfume, please? I brought it from home... This type of perfume can lift spirits. I often sniff at it when I feel down...

char_208_melan_CN_010.voiceText: Merry? Don't be so loud... The Doctor is very tired.

char_208_melan_CN_011.voiceText: Err... I-I'm Melantha... From now on, my blade is yours.

char_208_melan_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you very much... Um, did the others also get promoted? I think they all deserve it just like I do.

char_208_melan_CN_017.voiceText: Yeah... I will follow your orders.

char_208_melan_CN_018.voiceText: I'm... the leader? But I'm not particularly good at giving orders...

char_208_melan_CN_019.voiceText: Let's make the world a more peaceful place.

char_208_melan_CN_020.voiceText: Ansel... I'm counting on you now.

char_208_melan_CN_029.voiceText: No matter what difficulties are in store for me, I will keep on advancing.

char_208_melan_CN_030.voiceText: We won? Thank goodness for that...

char_208_melan_CN_032.voiceText: We failed... How did things end up this way...

char_208_melan_CN_033.voiceText: Is there... anyone else in here...?

char_208_melan_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, thank you for always taking care of me... Um, actually... I hope I can keep fighting.

char_209_ardign_CN_001.voiceText: Wahooo! It's my turn now, Doctor!

char_209_ardign_CN_002.voiceText: What does my 'Cardigan' code name mean? Aha! That's actually the name of my race. It's a family tradition to use it as a code name.

char_209_ardign_CN_003.voiceText: Wow, I found someone of my race on another team! I've got to invite her to hang out with me sometime!

char_209_ardign_CN_004.voiceText: I was born in the north of Leithanien, a place full of snow and forests. Oh, I can teach you how to ski!

char_209_ardign_CN_005.voiceText: A lot of people say stuff like 'it's a Defender's duty to strengthen her position,' but that's such an outdated idea. Speed is what you need! This is an era of nimble warfare! Slow down, and you'll be left behind!

char_209_ardign_CN_007.voiceText: *Sniff sniff*... I recognize this smell, it's gotta be Melantha! I hope we can become closer friends... Cause then, we'll be able to work better as a team!

char_209_ardign_CN_008.voiceText: Hehe, I really enjoy playing with kids. In my hometown, I took my brothers and sisters on a sled trip every year. I really miss it! Oh, speaking of sleds... I wonder if Adnachiel can make one for me.

char_209_ardign_CN_009.voiceText: I also have many things that I don't like. Like Oripathy, for instance... But there's no point in worrying too much. I would rather live my days in happiness! Plus, I've got you with me, Doctor!

char_209_ardign_CN_011.voiceText: Heeellooo! I've never been in such a huge mobile facility before! I'm so excited! Merry of the Cardigan here. Are you the Doctor?

char_209_ardign_CN_013.voiceText: Yay! I will keep fighting hard for my next promotion! I'm sure it will come in time!

char_209_ardign_CN_017.voiceText: Awesome! Finally, my time has come!

char_209_ardign_CN_018.voiceText: A-Ansel! Oh, come on! I promise I won't lead everyone on a wild-goose chase!

char_209_ardign_CN_019.voiceText: Formation ready! Move forward to the objective!

char_209_ardign_CN_020.voiceText: Let's go! ...Steward, what was I supposed to do next?

char_209_ardign_CN_021.voiceText: One must not hesitate on the battlefield!

char_209_ardign_CN_029.voiceText: I knew we could do it. Right, Adnachiel?

char_209_ardign_CN_031.voiceText: Kudos to the Medic team! You saved my life...

char_209_ardign_CN_033.voiceText: Steward, what should I do next?

char_209_ardign_CN_036.voiceText: Melantha? Huh? Why are you here, Doctor?!

char_210_stward_CN_001.voiceText: Welcome back, Doctor. Steward at your service.

char_210_stward_CN_002.voiceText: Steward is my last name, as well as my code name as an Operator. My surname shows what my ancestors did for a living.

char_210_stward_CN_003.voiceText: I didn't expect to meet someone from my race here. Is that kid looking for someone? I know how it feels... Oh, it's nothing.

char_210_stward_CN_004.voiceText: People often say our fur has the 'color of snow.' Doctor, have you ever seen snow?

char_210_stward_CN_005.voiceText: Ms. Lava has a very distinct fighting style. I thought she was going to cast with her book, but her real casting tool was a dagger. Her style reminds me of the psychic who taught me Arts.

char_210_stward_CN_007.voiceText: It is my honor to work for you, Doctor. I do hope you can find it in yourself to treat Ms. Melantha better. She's alone all the time...

char_210_stward_CN_008.voiceText: Adnachiel is a mysterious one... No one can tell what he is thinking.

char_210_stward_CN_009.voiceText: Ansel... Don't worry. I stopped caring about my identity as an Infected long ago. In fact, I received a lot of help because of it. Before the Infection takes away what's dear to me, I will use it to create a place where everyone can live in peace.

char_210_stward_CN_010.voiceText: Are you tired? Do take a good rest, Doctor. Rhodes Island will need your skills tomorrow.

char_210_stward_CN_011.voiceText: Caster Steward reporting in. I'm glad to be working with you.

char_210_stward_CN_012.voiceText: I have learned a lot. Thank you.

char_210_stward_CN_013.voiceText: I'm glad that you are satisfied with my work. Master Dobermann will be happy too.

char_210_stward_CN_017.voiceText: Hey everyone, what can I do for you?

char_210_stward_CN_018.voiceText: Cardigan, always read the situation before you take action.

char_210_stward_CN_019.voiceText: Well, I'll be sure to bring you some good news.

char_210_stward_CN_020.voiceText: They probably won't be able to survive the night.

char_210_stward_CN_029.voiceText: With the right strategy, we'll make it through any tight spot.

char_210_stward_CN_030.voiceText: A perfect victory. Good work, everyone!

char_210_stward_CN_031.voiceText: Ansel, please see if anyone is hurt and prepare for our next battle.

char_210_stward_CN_032.voiceText: Did we make a mistake somewhere...?

char_210_stward_CN_033.voiceText: Is that you, Cardigan? Hey, don't touch the equipment!

char_210_stward_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, is there anything I can do for you?

char_211_adnach_CN_001.voiceText: That device you're holding seems to be in poor shape. Would you mind if I took a look at it?

char_211_adnach_CN_002.voiceText: Hey, Ansel. Cardigan looks good today. Did you want something from me?

char_211_adnach_CN_003.voiceText: We have a squad of very interesting people, especially Melantha. She always seems to be hiding from me, but I can sniff her out.

char_211_adnach_CN_004.voiceText: Cardigan, what are you doing? You look so happy.

char_211_adnach_CN_005.voiceText: Not every Laterano has the right to use guns, rare weapons that they are. In my hometown, we're pretty good at making knockoff gun parts. The crossbow crafting industry is also on the rise. The result is what I have here - a crossbow with tactical rail attached.

char_211_adnach_CN_007.voiceText: Would you like to try some of my handmade sweets? I'm kind of ashamed that I can only make 25 types of desserts. It feels like I've disgraced the Laterano people.

char_211_adnach_CN_008.voiceText: What's wrong with my halo? I don't know why, but it seems to have deviated slightly. According to Dr. Kal'tsit, this is probably linked to my abnormal hippocampus.

char_211_adnach_CN_009.voiceText: Instead of watching you from afar, I feel much better standing by your side, Doctor.

char_211_adnach_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, you truly strike an impressive figure, even when you rest like that.

char_211_adnach_CN_011.voiceText: My name is Adnachiel. I'm a Sniper from Laterano. Although I'm not yet certified to carry a gun, I can match the veterans with my crossbow!

char_211_adnach_CN_012.voiceText: Put me to good use and I'll be more than happy.

char_211_adnach_CN_013.voiceText: Thank you very much for the promotion.

char_211_adnach_CN_018.voiceText: If anything breaks, bring it to me. I may be able to fix it for you.

char_211_adnach_CN_019.voiceText: It's time to go. Are you ready?

char_211_adnach_CN_029.voiceText: Everything went just as you planned, Doctor.

char_211_adnach_CN_030.voiceText: We have the Doctor's orders to thank for this.

char_211_adnach_CN_031.voiceText: Our operation was a success, but something feels a bit off...

char_211_adnach_CN_033.voiceText: This place has a great vibe.

char_211_adnach_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor? I'm so happy to be with you!

char_211_adnach_CN_042.voiceText: May the Lord bless you, Doctor.

char_212_ansel_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, it's time for your injection. Um, are, are you alright?! Are you scared of needles?

char_212_ansel_CN_002.voiceText: Like Master Kal'tsit is always telling you, Doctor, you really need some exercise. I'm new here, but you still need to listen to my advice.

char_212_ansel_CN_003.voiceText: Cardigan! If you move like that when you attack, you'll wind up getting hurt.

char_212_ansel_CN_004.voiceText: Good grief... Doctor, you need to care of yourself. Don't keep making us do it for you.

char_212_ansel_CN_005.voiceText: Are you worried about my health after so many night shifts? Don't worry. My race has a unique way of producing hormones which allows us to handle night activities better. This way, I can hand my shift over to Ms. Hibiscus at just the right time.

char_212_ansel_CN_007.voiceText: You must stop with the midnight snacks. Don't go bringing up my eating habits. I eat at night because of my racial traits! Yes, racial traits!

char_212_ansel_CN_008.voiceText: I am Ansel. This sounds a bit embarrassing, but I chose to become a Medic because I have been sickly since childhood. But now that I am an Operator, I will be sure not to be a burden to you. So please treat me just the same way you treat the others.

char_212_ansel_CN_009.voiceText: I know everyone did what they could. But I heard from Master Kal'tsit that Steward and Melantha's are not looking so good... My job is to make their lives as easy as possible. Doctor, let's redouble our efforts, together.

char_212_ansel_CN_010.voiceText: Adnachiel, could you ask Cardigan to settle down for a moment? The Doctor is resting.

char_212_ansel_CN_011.voiceText: I am Ansel, a medical intern. I will be assisting with surgery and internal medicine, among other forms. I look forward to working with you.

char_212_ansel_CN_012.voiceText: Hope I didn't cause you any trouble.

char_212_ansel_CN_013.voiceText: I'm glad that you care about the wellbeing of us Medics.

char_212_ansel_CN_018.voiceText: Medical support should be the top priority for any tactical squad.

char_212_ansel_CN_019.voiceText: Alright, all medicine has been prepared.

char_212_ansel_CN_020.voiceText: Injections ready. Please prepare for battle.

char_212_ansel_CN_026.voiceText: Your medication is here. Take it!

char_212_ansel_CN_029.voiceText: Phew, thank the Lord I brought enough medicine. Please don't worry.

char_212_ansel_CN_030.voiceText: I was very impressed by everyone's performance. It was fantastic.

char_212_ansel_CN_031.voiceText: Please hold on, I will treat your injuries right away.

char_212_ansel_CN_032.voiceText: We have injured! I need to get the wounded to the rear. Cover me!

char_212_ansel_CN_033.voiceText: Let me check the medical supplies here.

char_212_ansel_CN_034.voiceText: Whoa, Doctor, please don't mess with me!

char_212_ansel_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, I'm really glad that you like me.

char_108_silent_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, these are your tasks for the day. Yeah. A whole pile of work. Let's get to it.

char_108_silent_CN_002.voiceText: Is Ifrit making trouble again? Sorry. I'll discipline her later.

char_108_silent_CN_003.voiceText: Zzzzz... Huh? Um, I was taking a nap... I'm still not used to working during the day.

char_108_silent_CN_004.voiceText: My reasons for quitting Rhine Lab? So much happened since I signed on, I don't even know where to start...

char_108_silent_CN_005.voiceText: Have you ever heard of a woman named Saria? Like me, she was once a scientist at Rhine Lab, and she was one of the people responsible for the creation of Ifrit...

char_108_silent_CN_006.voiceText: Our biology research at Rhine Lab went so far as to implant Originium Shards into living bodies... Sorry, we'd better change the subject.

char_108_silent_CN_007.voiceText: Saria? You mean she's here at Rhodes Island too? Is she here for Ifrit...? She walked out without a second thought, so why has she returned...?!

char_108_silent_CN_008.voiceText: I will not allow Ifrit to see Saria. Please trust me, this is for Ifrit's own good...!

char_108_silent_CN_009.voiceText: Are you trying to cure Oripathy too? I heard that you were involved in the development of medical technology at Rhodes Island. Heheh... You may be what we researchers have been waiting for.

char_108_silent_CN_010.voiceText: ...Doctor, did you fall asleep? All right. Leave the rest of the work to me.

char_108_silent_CN_011.voiceText: I am Olivia Silence, an Originium scientist from the Rhine Lab Medical Research Institute. My hope is to rid the world of Oripathy... even if it means risking my life in the process.

char_108_silent_CN_012.voiceText: I will make good use of this new power.

char_108_silent_CN_013.voiceText: Is my medicine effective? Wonderful. This news brings me even greater joy than my promotion.

char_108_silent_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, I am looking forward to the day when the world is finally cured of Oripathy. In fighting and studying with you, I think that day may not be far off.

char_108_silent_CN_018.voiceText: Come on, team, let's fight with all our might.

char_108_silent_CN_019.voiceText: Is Originium to be blamed for this battle?

char_108_silent_CN_020.voiceText: Observe and determine the form of Infection. Such data will be useful for my experiments.

char_108_silent_CN_029.voiceText: In order to defeat stronger enemies, must we make further use of Originium's power...?

char_108_silent_CN_030.voiceText: Medical team, please take tissue samples from the Infected, we need to see the composition of the Infection in this area.

char_108_silent_CN_031.voiceText: All wounded personnel, please remain calm. The medical team will get to you.

char_108_silent_CN_032.voiceText: ...Now is not the time for despair. We must withdraw immediately.

char_108_silent_CN_033.voiceText: This room... No, this design makes me sleepy!

char_134_ifrit_CN_001.voiceText: Why is this office so damn cold?! Hey, I'mma burn it down, alright?

char_134_ifrit_CN_002.voiceText: Huh? Is this book expensive? Heehee. Call me Mistress Ifrit and I'll give it back to you!

char_134_ifrit_CN_003.voiceText: What? You want me to read this book? What I hate most is... What? Did... did Silence say so? Um... How... How is this word pronounced?

char_134_ifrit_CN_004.voiceText: I hate it when those dumbasses in white coats stare at me... Yeah, that means you! Jackass! Cut it out! Go stare at someone else!

char_134_ifrit_CN_005.voiceText: Um... I know! I won't scare people with fire anymore!

char_134_ifrit_CN_006.voiceText: Back down! You... Why are you getting so close to me? Are you going to put me on the lab table as well...?

char_134_ifrit_CN_007.voiceText: Saria's here? Let me talk to- Silence said I can't? C'mon, what's the big deal? Bring me to her and just keep it off the record!

char_134_ifrit_CN_008.voiceText: What's going on between Silence and Saria? I don't understand... Hey! You know how to get them to make up? Tell me... won't you?

char_134_ifrit_CN_009.voiceText: You can do whatever you like with me, but you better well be nice to Silence. When she wants something, you go get it for her! Do that, and I'll follow your orders from this day forward!

char_134_ifrit_CN_010.voiceText: You piece of...! Who said you could ignore me and take a goddamn nap?!

char_134_ifrit_CN_011.voiceText: You're in the presence of Ifrit! Silence told me Rhodes Island's a nice place, but I absolutely hate white-coat scientists like you people... well, Silence is an exception...

char_134_ifrit_CN_012.voiceText: Enhancing? Hmm, you mean you can make my flames burn brighter?

char_134_ifrit_CN_013.voiceText: What's this? Promotion Manual for Rhodes Island Operators? What the hell? Why are there so many rules after promotion? Screw this!

char_134_ifrit_CN_014.voiceText: Hee hee. That's right! I don't give a damn about those rules. All I know is that you need my help!

char_134_ifrit_CN_018.voiceText: I'm the captain? So, just do like Silence would, right?

char_134_ifrit_CN_019.voiceText: Hey! I'm the captain, which means I'M giving the orders here!

char_134_ifrit_CN_020.voiceText: Yo, how about a fiery barbecue!

char_134_ifrit_CN_024.voiceText: Hell loaded and ready to fire!

char_134_ifrit_CN_025.voiceText: Does it hurt? I bet it does!

char_134_ifrit_CN_027.voiceText: Nobody can hear you scream for help!

char_134_ifrit_CN_029.voiceText: I need more! Much more! I am invincible!

char_134_ifrit_CN_030.voiceText: I'll gladly burn those walking bags of trash into ash. It's gonna be real warm!

char_134_ifrit_CN_031.voiceText: Nothing but cinders left now. I could've done the job single-handedly!

char_134_ifrit_CN_032.voiceText: Damn... You... It's you who made me look stupid!

char_134_ifrit_CN_034.voiceText: What are you doing!? Let go of me!

char_134_ifrit_CN_036.voiceText: Heheh, you're surprisingly nice. Wanna play a game?

char_202_demkni_CN_001.voiceText: I've checked your schedule... Isn't it time you took a break? Excuse me, then.

char_202_demkni_CN_002.voiceText: All things are bound to evolution by the laws of nature. Yet Rhine Lab attempted to change it; take control of it, even. What a foolish plan...

char_202_demkni_CN_003.voiceText: As a researcher, have you ever participated in some experiments you probably shouldn't have? No? That's good.

char_202_demkni_CN_004.voiceText: Don't you think it's too noisy at Rhodes Island? A work environment must be quiet and focused. You should enforce discipline on your subordinates.

char_202_demkni_CN_005.voiceText: My true power has nothing to do with first aid. However, I have slightly adjusted the operation of this power to accommodate it to your command.

char_202_demkni_CN_006.voiceText: You think Calcification magic only makes organisms weaker? You're wrong. I can condense calcium into a tough enamel. Let the enemy try, no one can break my shield.

char_202_demkni_CN_007.voiceText: You've seen me fighting with Silence? Yes, we do that a lot... Sorry for causing you trouble, and Rhodes Island.

char_202_demkni_CN_008.voiceText: Please tell Ifrit on my behalf, 'No matter what happens, I will protect you'... Face her? No, I'm not ready for that.

char_202_demkni_CN_009.voiceText: Even in the most desperate of situations, I shall stand fast and make an everlasting impression to the people I hold dear. Such is my bottom line and my motto in life. You will do the same, won't you?

char_202_demkni_CN_010.voiceText: I'm going back to my room if you don't need me.

char_202_demkni_CN_011.voiceText: I am Saria, ex-member of the Rhine Lab Medical Research Institute Experiment Team. As for now... in order to lead those who have lost their way back onto the right path, I need Rhodes Island's assistance.

char_202_demkni_CN_013.voiceText: Listen, you must continue motivating your subordinates with your ideas if you hope to maintain influence over them.

char_202_demkni_CN_014.voiceText: Promotion? I don't want this to be some special treatment. However, for that girl's sake, I do need your help, until all those distorted rules are corrected...!

char_202_demkni_CN_017.voiceText: I am within my rights to have my own opinion on your command.

char_202_demkni_CN_018.voiceText: Let's have a briefing on the upcoming mission.

char_202_demkni_CN_019.voiceText: All Operators must maintain strict discipline.

char_202_demkni_CN_020.voiceText: Are they the ones that created the disaster and kindled the fire of war?

char_202_demkni_CN_025.voiceText: You're not strong enough to stop me.

char_202_demkni_CN_029.voiceText: Your tactics appear modern, yet the ideas behind them are primitive at their roots. Just what era do you stem from?

char_202_demkni_CN_030.voiceText: All must return to the existing order. None shall disobey the rules.

char_202_demkni_CN_031.voiceText: The routed enemies may be calling for reinforcements. We must hunt down every last one of them.

char_202_demkni_CN_033.voiceText: This room has interesting decor. I'd be more fond of a futuristic style, though.

char_202_demkni_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, you might do a bit of research into the past in your free time. You will find it most interesting, I'm sure.

char_128_plosis_CN_001.voiceText: Greetings, Doctor. How may I assist you?

char_128_plosis_CN_002.voiceText: Deep Sleep Mode enabled... Zzzzz... Switching to Power Saving Mode... Zzzzz...

char_128_plosis_CN_003.voiceText: Due to my racial traits and the infection's effect on my body, I may fall asleep in the midst of a conversation. Please pay it no mind.

char_128_plosis_CN_004.voiceText: I met Dr. Silence at Rhine Lab. I provided big data analysis and risk evaluation for her on a secret project.

char_128_plosis_CN_005.voiceText: Warning! Reverting Rhodes Island database to initial state... Don't worry. It's just a joke. Please don't panic.

char_128_plosis_CN_006.voiceText: I recommend you refactor my data if optimization fails to increase my performance. This will improve communication efficiency, and Ptilopsis will... Zzzz...

char_128_plosis_CN_007.voiceText: My manner of speaking? It is caused by Originium poisoning. By no means do I enjoy articulating my thoughts in this way.

char_128_plosis_CN_008.voiceText: Warning, system has recovered from a fatal error. Reconfiguring to last normal system bootup point. Please pay it no mind.

char_128_plosis_CN_009.voiceText: It is, in fact, quite burdensome to speak in this manner. But this is a necessary measure to prevent the system nexus from being devoured by that other voice. Doctor, if I become rampant, please guide me back onto the right path.

char_128_plosis_CN_010.voiceText: System... is now in Sleep Mode...

char_128_plosis_CN_011.voiceText: I am Ptilopsis, former data analyst of the Rhine Lab Medical Research Institute. Please submit your orders via the Command Line.

char_128_plosis_CN_013.voiceText: Finished installing update. Ptilopsis' system permissions have been revised.

char_128_plosis_CN_014.voiceText: Warning. Reverting Rhodes Island database to two years ago... Relax. It's just joke. System update completed.

char_128_plosis_CN_017.voiceText: Successfully built package using new data.

char_128_plosis_CN_019.voiceText: Direct memory access to application map and enemy coordinates set. Please wait.

char_128_plosis_CN_029.voiceText: Even such a difficult scenario couldn't stop you, Doctor. Perhaps one day you will find the solution for the non-deterministic polynomial time problem.

char_128_plosis_CN_030.voiceText: Your logical deduction was absolutely correct. What a perfect calculation.

char_128_plosis_CN_031.voiceText: A number of errors have been detected. Please confirm.

char_128_plosis_CN_032.voiceText: A fatal error has occured during the mission. Please reboot the system.

char_128_plosis_CN_033.voiceText: Is this place like a disk array?

char_128_plosis_CN_036.voiceText: Detecting affection increase for the Doctor within Ptilopsis. Would you like to skip to the next dialogue option?

char_128_plosis_CN_042.voiceText: It is a new day. The Doctor is now online. Detecting emotional surge within Ptilopsis.

char_242_otter_CN_001.voiceText: Structural design, industrial R&D, scientific research. You name it, and I can do it, Doctor.

char_242_otter_CN_002.voiceText: The Engineering Department never approve my proposals. Do they have any bias toward me? What should I do... Right! Doctor, would you please submit this suggestion on improvement for me? It's a deal then!

char_242_otter_CN_003.voiceText: There are many workshops like mine in Rhine Lab, but what takes others six weeks to finish, I can have it done in one. I'm not boasting!

char_242_otter_CN_004.voiceText: DO NOT interrupt me when I'm doing my research, or you'll have my Meeboos on your ass! And me!

char_242_otter_CN_005.voiceText: At night I'm always full of inspiration... and the urgency to sleep! No... I can't bear it... Where's the pillow... I need to rest...

char_242_otter_CN_006.voiceText: Hm? Why are these cuties called Meeboos? That's because they go 'meeee-boooo' when they boot up. So I named them after that. Fitting, don't you think? Just listen and you'll get it. You press this switch to... WHUAH?! Wrong one! That's the self-destruct button! Oh shoot, run awaaaaaay!

char_242_otter_CN_007.voiceText: That girl who just passed by... that was Silence, right? If only then... Oh, sorry, the non-disclosure agreement is still in effect. I should keep my mouth shut.

char_242_otter_CN_008.voiceText: I feel kinda empty when I've got nothing to do... I guess that's just how engineers are. You know how that's like, right, Doctor? Huh? You don't?

char_242_otter_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, may I request... No! Not 10 square meters! I asked too much last time, so this time... all I need is 3 square meters! Don't... Don't you leave, Doctor! Even 1 square meter for my research will do! Please!

char_242_otter_CN_010.voiceText: Geez... where's the coffeemaker... Oh, there it is... You want some too, Doctor?

char_242_otter_CN_011.voiceText: I am the Lutra Workshop of Rhine Lab, at your service. Yup, I said 'workshop,' but it's just me. I'm the whole workshop. Am I amazing or what?

char_242_otter_CN_012.voiceText: This structure... Interesting. I'll look into it.

char_242_otter_CN_013.voiceText: This raise came just in time! I can afford to upgrade my equipment now.

char_242_otter_CN_014.voiceText: I promised I'd show you progress one day, didn't I? Look at what I have! Isn't it nice?

char_242_otter_CN_018.voiceText: Commanding both Operators and my Meeboos at the same time is a bit much even for me...

char_242_otter_CN_019.voiceText: Hopefully we can get some useful experiment data!

char_242_otter_CN_020.voiceText: Come on, Meeboo, show them what Rhine Lab's technology can do!

char_242_otter_CN_027.voiceText: If anything breaks, I can just make another one!

char_242_otter_CN_028.voiceText: My Meeboos are more than just machines!

char_242_otter_CN_029.voiceText: Come on, Meeboo! Show everyone your victory dance!

char_242_otter_CN_030.voiceText: Nice! We practically rolled over them!

char_242_otter_CN_031.voiceText: The device is slightly damaged. I'll fix it in no time.

char_242_otter_CN_032.voiceText: Oh no! My Meeboo...! I'll need to make more...

char_242_otter_CN_033.voiceText: Now I want a new workshop!

char_242_otter_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, let me touch your head and give you some inspiration!

char_215_mantic_CN_001.voiceText: Umm... I've been here... for two hours now...

char_215_mantic_CN_002.voiceText: Sorry... it doesn't really feel like I'm here... But that's not because of my power...

char_215_mantic_CN_003.voiceText: My power is to... become undetectable to people... in certain environments...

char_215_mantic_CN_004.voiceText: I've never had any friends... I mean, who wants a friend that they can't even see...

char_215_mantic_CN_005.voiceText: My tail... will curl up when out of battle... So don't be afraid...

char_215_mantic_CN_006.voiceText: Doctor... leave the dangerous work to me... After all... my power was made for that...

char_215_mantic_CN_007.voiceText: I collected these... ID tags I have around my neck... Holding onto such proof of other people's existence... is something... I enjoy...

char_215_mantic_CN_008.voiceText: Don't let that girl named 'Nightmare' near me... She's... dangerous... My power... doesn't work on her... Why...

char_215_mantic_CN_009.voiceText: I... I really want to cure my illness. However, I'm afraid... to lose my power... if I am cured... Will I still be of use then...?

char_215_mantic_CN_010.voiceText: I hate the loneliness... of being ignored...

char_215_mantic_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Manticore... My power is to kill people silently... Don't be afraid, you're not... my target...

char_215_mantic_CN_012.voiceText: Thank you... And please, keep me company...

char_215_mantic_CN_013.voiceText: I've waited for this promotion... I always thought... that my power wasn't good enough...

char_215_mantic_CN_014.voiceText: I'm... helpful to you... right? I don't have anywhere else to go... My home is here... at Rhodes Island... Please... let me protect it with you...

char_215_mantic_CN_018.voiceText: Nobody will like me... as their captain...

char_215_mantic_CN_020.voiceText: Please use tactics that utilize my power... even if it's a cowardly one... I don't mind...

char_215_mantic_CN_027.voiceText: I don't... like doing this... either...

char_215_mantic_CN_029.voiceText: Even on such a terrifying battlefield... you kept a clear head and made good decisions. You're awesome, Doctor...!

char_215_mantic_CN_030.voiceText: I'll do whatever it takes to win... I suppose...

char_215_mantic_CN_031.voiceText: Let me take care of... the ones that got away...

char_215_mantic_CN_032.voiceText: I'm sorry... It's all my fault...

char_215_mantic_CN_036.voiceText: Thank you for paying attention to me... I know it's your duty... but it still makes me happy...!

char_149_scave_CN_001.voiceText: Better get your job done quicker than waste time on chitchat.

char_149_scave_CN_002.voiceText: You'd better remember that failing to adapt makes you a useless burden.

char_149_scave_CN_003.voiceText: Work, eat, run, repeat. Big fricking whoop. That's just how life is for most people these days.

char_149_scave_CN_004.voiceText: My job was to take care of 'inconveniences' for my employers. Somehow that turned into them calling me Scavenger.

char_149_scave_CN_005.voiceText: Just like the two sides of a coin, no matter how splendid the face is, the backside is always stained with dirt.

char_149_scave_CN_006.voiceText: I've adapted to this place really well since I first joined? Pfft, are you joking? I've just gotten used to working on the surface.

char_149_scave_CN_007.voiceText: That's Provence, isn't it... The girl who got Infected while helping people during a Catastrophe... Look at that massive tail she's got...

char_149_scave_CN_008.voiceText: You know, Doctor... I initially hated the idea of working with other people. I figured our methods would clash. But at some point, I came to realize that's not the case.

char_149_scave_CN_009.voiceText: If only she were still alive... Now all I can do is live alone, carrying her dreams on my back.

char_149_scave_CN_010.voiceText: How can you sleep so soundly when you're defenseless...

char_149_scave_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Scavenger. Leave the dirty work to me. Just pay what I'm owed and we'll be good.

char_149_scave_CN_013.voiceText: This still isn't enough. I need to become stronger...

char_149_scave_CN_014.voiceText: Thanks, Doctor. I feel like I have a reason to fight now.

char_149_scave_CN_017.voiceText: Do I need to quip just 'cause I joined the team?

char_149_scave_CN_019.voiceText: Conceal yourselves so the enemy won't find you.

char_149_scave_CN_027.voiceText: There is no turning back for you!

char_149_scave_CN_030.voiceText: Hah. This is what their weakness gets them.

char_149_scave_CN_031.voiceText: Tch, some of them got away. I'm disappointed if that's all you can do.

char_149_scave_CN_033.voiceText: Just give me a dark corner.

char_149_scave_CN_036.voiceText: You want me to dispose of you too?

char_149_scave_CN_042.voiceText: You got a job for me?

char_204_platnm_CN_001.voiceText: *Yaaawn*... Doctor, could I take a quick break?

char_204_platnm_CN_002.voiceText: Don't worry about my bow. I keep it well maintained. It's much tougher than you, so stop asking about it already.

char_204_platnm_CN_003.voiceText: There are so many interesting people at Rhodes Island. Would be nice if I could make a friend or two to travel with.

char_204_platnm_CN_004.voiceText: Nowadays, the Knights of Kazimierz are little more than a bunch of musclehead jocks, or clowns obsessed with their own reputation. Man, it's so lame.

char_204_platnm_CN_005.voiceText: I was planning to return home after finishing this job, but now I've changed my mind. Why, you ask? You should know better than to ask a girl a question like that.

char_204_platnm_CN_006.voiceText: Want to know the origin of my codename? See, there are different ranks for the Knight Assassins in Kazimierz. There's three Darksteel and two Lazurite assassins above me, but I and I alone bear the rank of Platinum, from now till the day I die. So I figured it'd make a good codename.

char_204_platnm_CN_007.voiceText: Ah, it's Miss Nearl! No, no, I wasn't going to lay a hand on her. I'm just worried she's going to charge at me with her hammer.

char_204_platnm_CN_008.voiceText: Kazimierz is... a boring place. *Sigh*, I'm almost mad at how much more amusing life here at Rhodes Island is.

char_204_platnm_CN_009.voiceText: Have you thought about how you're going to maintain your relations with everyone here at Rhodes Island? You know, all suits of armor have small gaps which leave you vulnerable, and that's where the enemies always try to jam their blades. One hit to your weak point can bring down everything you've painstakingly built.

char_204_platnm_CN_010.voiceText: I'm so bored. Hoping something amusing happens.

char_204_platnm_CN_011.voiceText: Assassin of the Armorless Union of Kazimierz here as per our agreement. What am I called? Hmm... Call me Platinum, then. Nice to meet you.

char_204_platnm_CN_012.voiceText: Good. My bow feels even lighter. Thank you.

char_204_platnm_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? Isn't the rank of Platinum already intimidating enough? Oh, you are an interesting one.

char_204_platnm_CN_014.voiceText: Hah. Do you have the guts to gaze upon my true face, my dear Doctor?

char_204_platnm_CN_018.voiceText: Really? I'm commanding? It's not my strongest suit, but all right.

char_204_platnm_CN_019.voiceText: Will this battle be an interesting one?

char_204_platnm_CN_020.voiceText: You may as well attack all at once. You're all too weak anyway.

char_204_platnm_CN_029.voiceText: Nice. I had quite an enjoyable time.

char_204_platnm_CN_030.voiceText: Checkmate. I'm sorry, but victory is mine.

char_204_platnm_CN_031.voiceText: What a pity that we left some alive.

char_204_platnm_CN_032.voiceText: Don't give up... He who laughs last laughs best.

char_204_platnm_CN_033.voiceText: The atmosphere here is surprisingly good.

char_204_platnm_CN_036.voiceText: Want to go on a walk? If you're busy, there's always next time.

char_172_svrash_CN_001.voiceText: There are better ways to kill time. Care to try one?

char_172_svrash_CN_002.voiceText: Stop looking so serious all the time. Can't you at least smile when I'm around...? Good. That's what I want to see... Nobody better suited to solve your problems than me... Isn't that right?

char_172_svrash_CN_003.voiceText: That girl... Amiya, I believe her name was? She's no ordinary girl. If you don't put shackles on her wrists today, you will find yourself placing a crown upon her head tomorrow.

char_172_svrash_CN_004.voiceText: The stability of the alliance between Karlan and Rhodes Island depends solely on your state of mind, and mine. As such, we should at least try to get along, my friend.

char_172_svrash_CN_005.voiceText: I suppose... it's high time I signed this contract. Of course, I do know that the terms are in your, and Rhodes Island's favor.

char_172_svrash_CN_006.voiceText: I'm well aware this contract offers me nothing... What does that matter? I shall accept this unequal treaty nonetheless. The reason being that I, SilverAsh, recognize that you warrant it.

char_172_svrash_CN_007.voiceText: Is Ensia giving you trouble? My apologies. It was originally my responsibility to foster and guide her, but it's unlikely I will be able to do so. So I must ask... could you do it in my stead, {@nickname}?

char_172_svrash_CN_008.voiceText: Could you show me to Rhodes Island's deck? No, I'd just like to get a view of the area. Tenzin needs to spread his wings every once in a while as well. He must be longing to soar through the night sky.

char_172_svrash_CN_009.voiceText: If this continues, eventually there will come a day when you and I confront one another... I seem happy about that, you say? Hah, perhaps I am. You would be a worthy opponent, that's for certain. Let us make the most of our time left before that day comes.

char_172_svrash_CN_010.voiceText: 'When the aether darkens, 'tis an omen that snowfall draws near...'

char_172_svrash_CN_011.voiceText: I, SilverAsh, have joined your cause as a sworn ally. Whatever your plans may be, do not disappoint me.

char_172_svrash_CN_012.voiceText: For one to travel such an arduous path, they absolutely must have experience.

char_172_svrash_CN_013.voiceText: Ostentatious titles are one thing, but the trust accompanying them is what I care about. You surely know that.

char_172_svrash_CN_014.voiceText: It takes a daring person to drag me into their war. That being so, I, SilverAsh, will show my prowess for all of Rhodes Island to see.

char_172_svrash_CN_017.voiceText: We all have our roles to play. Use my abilities as best you see fit.

char_172_svrash_CN_018.voiceText: You want me to act as your proxy? Very well. But you must pay me due tribute later.

char_172_svrash_CN_019.voiceText: Compassion saves no one on the battlefield.

char_172_svrash_CN_020.voiceText: Show me what you're made of. Amuse me, if you even can.

char_172_svrash_CN_025.voiceText: 'The fool flaunting his gallantry reaches none with his vanity...'

char_172_svrash_CN_026.voiceText: 'Fool, for what reason hast thou come?'

char_172_svrash_CN_027.voiceText: 'Art thou mine worthy enemy, or art thou naught but a jester?'

char_172_svrash_CN_029.voiceText: The fiercer the battle, the more jubilant victory shall be.

char_172_svrash_CN_030.voiceText: A satisfying battle. It even brought palpitations to my heart.

char_172_svrash_CN_032.voiceText: Retreat at once, while there still is time.

char_172_svrash_CN_033.voiceText: For a place to rest my feet, it is acceptable.

char_172_svrash_CN_036.voiceText: Let me rest for just a while. I'm more tired than I thought. My apologies.

char_172_svrash_CN_042.voiceText: You haven't changed one bit, my friend.

char_173_slchan_CN_001.voiceText: Uh... Doctor, you really need to work out more, you know.

char_173_slchan_CN_002.voiceText: Everyone's really nice here at Rhodes Island. Too nice to prank. Oh, is it time for lunch? I'll help!

char_173_slchan_CN_003.voiceText: Mountaineering's not just a hobby of mine, it's my job! You heard me: job!

char_173_slchan_CN_004.voiceText: The hoop on my leg? Oh, you mean what it's for? It's just for decoration. I've got this crystal over here, see. Wanna touch?

char_173_slchan_CN_005.voiceText: Did my brother send Matterhorn to protect me? Aw, why couldn't he just come out and say he's worried about me?

char_173_slchan_CN_006.voiceText: I've always wanted to climb the holy Mt. Karlan, and I've only wanted it even more since my sister left us and became the Saintess. So Doctor, train me more, yeah? So one day I can reach the peak of Mt. Karlan and bring my sister home.

char_173_slchan_CN_007.voiceText: When it comes to hiking, I won't lose to anyone! No one knows these tools better than me. They make great weapons too!

char_173_slchan_CN_008.voiceText: Yeah, Oripathy really changed me. But if I keep wallowing in self-pity, that wouldn't be like me, right? So, no matter what lies in wait in the future... I should continue working hard on my chosen path.

char_173_slchan_CN_009.voiceText: Ah, it's snowing... We Silverashes can't go back to the way we were... I get that. Everything's changed. Only the snow is the same—the same snowflakes that I watched falling back home.

char_173_slchan_CN_010.voiceText: Doctoooor? Doctooooor! Heeeey! Fine, if you're just gonna sleep, then so be it. Bye-bye!

char_173_slchan_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Cliffheart, the one who dreams to touch the sky! Nice to meet you!

char_173_slchan_CN_013.voiceText: Promotion? Wow! Let's celebrate with some cake. Look, I grabbed these from Logistics. It's fine!

char_173_slchan_CN_014.voiceText: Well, well, you really know what you're doing, Doctor! That's right, I'm really talented. You'd better use my power well!

char_173_slchan_CN_017.voiceText: All right? I'm feeling motivated! Time to climb all the way to the top!

char_173_slchan_CN_018.voiceText: Eh? You want me to lead? This is all so sudden...

char_173_slchan_CN_019.voiceText: No more reckless Cliffheart. I'm serious from now on.

char_173_slchan_CN_020.voiceText: I'll show them what I can do!

char_173_slchan_CN_026.voiceText: My hook never misses! I've got this!

char_173_slchan_CN_027.voiceText: Amateurs are doomed to fall to their death!

char_173_slchan_CN_029.voiceText: There ain't no mountain too high, no situation too bleak!

char_173_slchan_CN_030.voiceText: Of course we won with me around!

char_173_slchan_CN_031.voiceText: Wow, they sure are good at running away!

char_173_slchan_CN_033.voiceText: It's so warm here... I'll hang out over here for a while!

char_173_slchan_CN_036.voiceText: Let me teach you all about hiking next time, Doctor! You'll love it, I promise!

char_174_slbell_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? You're here to pray? Sorry, I'm busy right now.

char_174_slbell_CN_002.voiceText: Hm? Yes, I'm the current Karlan Saintess. But I can be swamped by work, too. Who doesn't deserve to relax from time to time, right?

char_174_slbell_CN_003.voiceText: Wasting time on trivial affairs is what I call slacking off. What I'm doing right now is not slacking off! It's called taking the opportunity to recharge.

char_174_slbell_CN_004.voiceText: Work hard, play hard, right? Don't force all those rigid rules on me.

char_174_slbell_CN_005.voiceText: The Karlan Goddess? We're pretty good friends since we have to meet up for work a lot.

char_174_slbell_CN_006.voiceText: I'd be happy to help you, but the life of a Karlan Saintess is a busy one. Well, fine, I'll make an exception for you this once, but do remember that I don't have a lot of time to spare.

char_174_slbell_CN_007.voiceText: Meh, that Ensia... you people at Rhodes Island are all pretty fond of her, right? So it's not like she received any special treatment. And now... well, I think I get it now. It's fine like this. I'll just keep watching over her. It's fine.

char_174_slbell_CN_008.voiceText: I twisted my ankle once when I was a kid. My brother carried me on his back all night, going from house to house until someone agreed to take us in. I decided that very moment that I wanted to grow up to become someone like my brother! But now... heh, forget it.

char_174_slbell_CN_009.voiceText: Oh? How did you find me? I'll freeze your toes—huh? Coffee? For me? Thanks. Oh, right, Doctor, wanna hang out here with me for a while? The view is pretty nice. But let's keep it a secret, okay? A secret between just the two of us—aw, this coffee is so bitter!

char_174_slbell_CN_010.voiceText: It's rare to get to rest like this.

char_174_slbell_CN_011.voiceText: Shh, I sneaked out—oh, um, hi, HR Director! I... I'm here to lend my powers to Rhodes Island. Pramanix, Karlan Saintess, at your service. Bless you, my friend.

char_174_slbell_CN_012.voiceText: I hear a voice... repeating something in my head...

char_174_slbell_CN_013.voiceText: 'You shall emerge victorious one day.' This is the pledge of Karlan, and what I'm praying for as well.

char_174_slbell_CN_014.voiceText: Since when did you need blessings too? Can you wait a bit? I'll get ready.

char_174_slbell_CN_017.voiceText: May the Holy Mt. Karlan be with us.

char_174_slbell_CN_018.voiceText: Follow the jingling bells and you'll find the way.

char_174_slbell_CN_019.voiceText: Let me pray towards the mountains for you.

char_174_slbell_CN_026.voiceText: Here come the bells, the cold wind swirling by my feet.

char_174_slbell_CN_027.voiceText: These powers are a gift from the Holy Mountain.

char_174_slbell_CN_028.voiceText: As the bells ring, the impenetrable armor shall be no more.

char_174_slbell_CN_029.voiceText: It was simple, thanks to the Spirits' power.

char_174_slbell_CN_030.voiceText: The light of Karlan was shining on us.

char_174_slbell_CN_031.voiceText: If only we could have won without bloodshed—ah, forget it.

char_174_slbell_CN_032.voiceText: We must retreat! We are in danger!

char_174_slbell_CN_036.voiceText: Close your eyes and I'll bring you somewhere new... hey, keep your eyes closed!

char_198_blackd_CN_001.voiceText: It's not the duty of a guard to stand there and do nothing. How about we chat a bit?

char_198_blackd_CN_002.voiceText: With perfect positioning and a suitable environment, my letters should arrive without problem. After all, it's my job, right? I need to do well to survive.

char_198_blackd_CN_003.voiceText: Are you hungry? If you want something to eat, just say the word. I can't compete with Matterhorn in the kitchen, but I can at least cook a decent meal.

char_198_blackd_CN_004.voiceText: The comms equipment here at Rhodes Island is way too good. At this rate, I'm going to lose my job...

char_198_blackd_CN_005.voiceText: Anything else you need? Just don't keep me on the line for too long.

char_198_blackd_CN_006.voiceText: Huh? There's a faint smell on the letters? No way, you must be imagining things.

char_198_blackd_CN_007.voiceText: I owe my life to Sir SilverAsh. If necessary, I'll do anything for him.

char_198_blackd_CN_008.voiceText: You want me to transport... all these? That's a lot, Doctor! Come on, I'm no miracle maker!

char_198_blackd_CN_009.voiceText: Seems I'm no match for you. I suppose it's time to retire my business smile for now... *Ahem*... Hopefully from now on, I can show my true stripes when I stand with you.

char_198_blackd_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, there's a new message for... Ah, never mind.

char_198_blackd_CN_011.voiceText: Esteemed Leader of Rhodes Island, your ally—Courier of the Snow Realm—is here at your service. If you ever get into trouble during your contract with Sir SilverAsh, just snap your fingers and I'll come.

char_198_blackd_CN_012.voiceText: Whoa, that's an incredible job well done.

char_198_blackd_CN_013.voiceText: You'd save a lot of trouble if you send me onto the battlefield.

char_198_blackd_CN_014.voiceText: As the messenger of the Snow Realm, I'll definitely appear by your side when you need me.

char_198_blackd_CN_017.voiceText: Leave the scouting of the battlefield to me, then.

char_198_blackd_CN_018.voiceText: I won't blemish the name of the Snow Realm.

char_198_blackd_CN_019.voiceText: Too bad some people just can't let everyone live in peace.

char_198_blackd_CN_020.voiceText: They'll pay for their evil deeds.

char_198_blackd_CN_029.voiceText: I'll bring news of our victory to Rhodes Island right away!

char_198_blackd_CN_030.voiceText: Let's go grab a nice dinner after we clean up the battlefield. My treat!

char_198_blackd_CN_031.voiceText: Anyone injured? I've got medicine and bandages.

char_198_blackd_CN_032.voiceText: Let's get outta here first. Here, this way! Hurry!

char_198_blackd_CN_033.voiceText: I'll greet my roommates and neighbors first.

char_198_blackd_CN_036.voiceText: All right, I'll whip up a meal for you later.

char_198_blackd_CN_042.voiceText: Call me whenever you have need of me.

char_199_yak_CN_001.voiceText: I've moved your goods to where you need them. No worries, they weren't heavy.

char_199_yak_CN_002.voiceText: The shield is a symbol of a steadfast guardian.

char_199_yak_CN_003.voiceText: I've been in charge of protecting Young Master SilverAsh... I mean, Master SilverAsh... ever since he was young.

char_199_yak_CN_004.voiceText: It's not exactly polite to discuss this behind her back, but... Miss Enya... she really deserves a better life.

char_199_yak_CN_005.voiceText: I have heard that, if my shield were to ever get damaged, I should take it to Vulcan for repairs. This is true, yes?

char_199_yak_CN_006.voiceText: That was unexpected. The craftsmaster's truly a skilled one. I gotta thank her properly.

char_199_yak_CN_007.voiceText: Life at Rhodes Island is fun. The Snow Realm is rather bland in comparison.

char_199_yak_CN_008.voiceText: Master did send me to protect Ensia... but I honestly don't think she's the type who would sit there and ask to be protected.

char_199_yak_CN_009.voiceText: I am slowly starting to understand why Master SilverAsh holds you in such high regard.

char_199_yak_CN_010.voiceText: Sometimes, I start missing my life in the Snow Realm all of a sudden.

char_199_yak_CN_011.voiceText: Ally, I salute you in true Snow Realm fashion. I am codename Matterhorn, one of the guards dispatched here by Master SilverAsh.

char_199_yak_CN_013.voiceText: Thanks for the approval. I truly do not deserve it.

char_199_yak_CN_014.voiceText: I will not step back, not even if this shield shatters the very next second. Not because of my loyalty, but because of my conviction.

char_199_yak_CN_026.voiceText: I'm not here just for show!

char_199_yak_CN_027.voiceText: In order to remain loyal, I will become a demon if necessary!

char_199_yak_CN_029.voiceText: I haven't even shown my true colors yet.

char_199_yak_CN_030.voiceText: Their attacks feel like scratches on the surface to me.

char_199_yak_CN_031.voiceText: I promise I'll pull off a perfect victory next time! For your sake!

char_199_yak_CN_032.voiceText: So this is the price one pays for negligence...!

char_199_yak_CN_033.voiceText: Very nice room, this one. Furnished tastefully and has a peaceful atmosphere.

char_199_yak_CN_036.voiceText: This is my signature dish. How do you like it?

char_219_meteo_CN_001.voiceText: I'm on my shift right now. If I'm interrupting your work, I can go outside and wait there.

char_219_meteo_CN_002.voiceText: Did you investigate all the new Operators and check if their data lines up with their personal files?

char_219_meteo_CN_003.voiceText: No place in the world is absolutely safe as long as the war is still going on. Not even Rhodes Island! Please remember that.

char_219_meteo_CN_004.voiceText: To be frank, you're surrounded by people from all walks of life. That can be quite dangerous, don't you think?

char_219_meteo_CN_005.voiceText: I'm surprised that so many other Sarkazians like me have come to Rhodes Island—and they actually get along!

char_219_meteo_CN_006.voiceText: My bowgun may not be easy to operate, but it's just as powerful as the guns of the Lateranos. With it, I will defend the glory of my people.

char_219_meteo_CN_007.voiceText: I met Firewatch. That kid... she's using the name of the organization which we fought together in as her codename. It's like time has stopped for her ever since the day her hometown was destroyed...

char_219_meteo_CN_008.voiceText: As for what happened between Firewatch and I... she'll tell you when she's ready. All I can say is that I was not the one who led the rebel army to her hometown... but no one would believe the words of a Sarkazian, right?

char_219_meteo_CN_009.voiceText: I have my mission, and she has hers—to revenge. Even though we've met again at Rhodes Island, it probably won't affect anything. Our paths will probably not cross.

char_219_meteo_CN_010.voiceText: What's that sound? Is someone monitoring this room? Or am I just imagining things?

char_219_meteo_CN_011.voiceText: Codename Meteorite, a freelance mercenary. I'm a Sarkazian, as you can see. You still wanna hire me in spite of that?

char_219_meteo_CN_012.voiceText: My aim with my bowgun has improved.

char_219_meteo_CN_013.voiceText: You want to promote me? I see that I made the right choice to work here.

char_219_meteo_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you so much for this, really. I can't believe someone like me could receive a stable job here at Rhodes Island. I'll do everything I can to repay you for trusting in me.

char_219_meteo_CN_018.voiceText: Me, a leader? But I'm not that good at giving orders...

char_219_meteo_CN_019.voiceText: I'll do my best to take care of everyone.

char_219_meteo_CN_020.voiceText: Enemy status confirmed. Get ready to fight.

char_219_meteo_CN_029.voiceText: I don't want to see all these collapsing buildings, burning from the war. Please, let's just end this once and for all...

char_219_meteo_CN_030.voiceText: Think you can escape from my intricate net? Don't be silly.

char_219_meteo_CN_031.voiceText: Someone's escaped. Not the time to let our guard down.

char_219_meteo_CN_032.voiceText: Retreat! Get back to the stronghold and regroup.

char_158_milu_CN_001.voiceText: I'm keeping an eye on our surroundings. So far everything seems fine.

char_158_milu_CN_002.voiceText: You should know that some of those eyes on you hold nothing but malice. You're not safe, not even at Rhodes Island.

char_158_milu_CN_003.voiceText: Don't be afraid of those hostiles hiding in the shadow. No matter how those criminals try to hide, they can't escape my eyes.

char_158_milu_CN_004.voiceText: I'll have my revenge... even if I must lose my life for it.

char_158_milu_CN_005.voiceText: My clan, my friends, they all perished in the woods of our hometown... The only ones who mourned them were the trees, which gave unto them their leaves.

char_158_milu_CN_006.voiceText: This crossbow is manufactured for the sole purpose of punishing sinners. The day will come when I use it to pass my final judgement on those who deserve it.

char_158_milu_CN_007.voiceText: Meteorite... we used to be friends. On the day my hometown was destroyed, we were part of the small group that managed to escape.

char_158_milu_CN_008.voiceText: Since then, I've never stopped searching for the traitor who led the rebel army to our town. Could it be Meteorite? No, I don't think so...

char_158_milu_CN_009.voiceText: ...Oh, did I fall asleep? S-sorry, I've been spending more time patrolling these days, so... It's fine, you say? But... um, thank you for caring.

char_158_milu_CN_010.voiceText: I'd like to take a nap...

char_158_milu_CN_011.voiceText: Firewatch here. I'm a sniper. To avenge my fallen clan, I need all the power I can get.

char_158_milu_CN_013.voiceText: Thanks for appointing me to this position.

char_158_milu_CN_014.voiceText: Thank you for the promotion. I hope you'll keep using my powers for the right thing. But if you won't...

char_158_milu_CN_020.voiceText: Enemies spotted. Taking action at once.

char_158_milu_CN_029.voiceText: I'm not done until I have my revenge...

char_158_milu_CN_031.voiceText: Battle over. Commence search for surviving hostiles.

char_158_milu_CN_033.voiceText: I'm not used to being in a room with so many people...

char_158_milu_CN_036.voiceText: Uh, please don't touch my antlers... it tickles...

char_115_headbr_CN_001.voiceText: I'm here to help. So? Whose ass are we kicking next?

char_115_headbr_CN_002.voiceText: You can't go out without permission? Come on, aren't you the one in charge? Anyway, come on, let's go out.

char_115_headbr_CN_003.voiceText: Did you say something? Sorry, had my headphones on.

char_115_headbr_CN_004.voiceText: The leader of Rhodes Island looks younger than even Istina. How can you let a kid like that onto the battlefield? How?

char_115_headbr_CN_005.voiceText: Why do I stare at you all the time? Cause I'm observing what you're up to.

char_115_headbr_CN_006.voiceText: It's every soldier's goal to make it to the top. You saying I should feel bad for wanting to take your position?

char_115_headbr_CN_007.voiceText: Plans for the future? Don't have any. You got a problem with that? I'm still young, no need to plan far ahead.

char_115_headbr_CN_008.voiceText: I found Istina and her gang along my travels. They had some company, but I dealt with them. Had no choice, they refused to behave themselves.

char_115_headbr_CN_009.voiceText: Huh? Chernobog? Who'd ever wanna go back to that miserable city? Rhodes Island is where our new lives begin. So, let's keep it tight, Doctor.

char_115_headbr_CN_010.voiceText: We really got nothing left to do?

char_115_headbr_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Zima, leader of the Independent Ursus Student Union. I can make do without one, but my comrades need a place to call home. Let's cut the crap, gimme a job to do. I know lodging ain't free in this place.

char_115_headbr_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? Cool. So I'll keep getting promoted if I keep doing a good job in battle, yeah?

char_115_headbr_CN_014.voiceText: I'll be frank: if I keep getting promoted, I might end up replacing you someday. Oh, you think I'm joking? Listen, pal, I'm dead serious here.

char_115_headbr_CN_017.voiceText: Make me the leader or just a team member, either way's fine by me.

char_115_headbr_CN_018.voiceText: What a pain in my ass.

char_115_headbr_CN_025.voiceText: The hell are you scared of!

char_115_headbr_CN_028.voiceText: You wanna win, or you wanna die?!

char_115_headbr_CN_029.voiceText: Anyone with a death wish left out there? Come out and I'll oblige you!

char_115_headbr_CN_031.voiceText: Well, this place is ours now.

char_115_headbr_CN_032.voiceText: Man, you guys suck. Get lost!

char_115_headbr_CN_033.voiceText: What do you want me to do here?

char_115_headbr_CN_036.voiceText: Hey, you're getting better at giving orders these days. You're starting to see the fun in fighting, eh?

char_195_glassb_CN_001.voiceText: Hello, I'm on duty right now. You don't seem happy about it... Do I look that unreliable to you?
