Though our definitions of 'protect' have nothing in common with each other, I will be standing here, until the very end. We are unable to forget the past, but a different future may await you.

char_003_kalts_CN_010.voiceText: Are you awake, or still in a dream?

char_003_kalts_CN_011.voiceText: Doctor, my appearance here indicates that the situation has turned for the worse. You must concentrate... on continuing to accomplish your mission.

char_003_kalts_CN_013.voiceText: The stronger, the more fragile. That is the principle of all living things.

char_003_kalts_CN_014.voiceText: Mon3tr and I will protect everyone. Especially you, Doctor.

char_003_kalts_CN_017.voiceText: I will see you all through.

char_003_kalts_CN_018.voiceText: Now you need only devote yourself to operation planning.

char_003_kalts_CN_020.voiceText: Are combat plans ready? Everyone, interception formation.

char_003_kalts_CN_022.voiceText: Have your deployment optimally worked out.

char_003_kalts_CN_029.voiceText: Ensure video records of this battle are processed for database storage purposes.

char_003_kalts_CN_030.voiceText: Mon3tr, collect my necessary tissue samples.

char_003_kalts_CN_031.voiceText: Assess the danger factor of those fleeing, as well as the possibility of a reprise attack from enemy forces.

char_003_kalts_CN_032.voiceText: Secure evac route. Prepare to operate!

char_003_kalts_CN_033.voiceText: How has the infrastructure here been coming along?

char_003_kalts_CN_036.voiceText: You seem to have grown used to your own work and responsibility. You've become much like a leader.

char_474_glady_CN_001.voiceText: Please leave for the moment. I will not permit any disturbance as I work. I appreciate your understanding.

char_474_glady_CN_002.voiceText: I wish to avoid unnecessary headaches. On that point, we stand together. Given your rich experience, I am certain you are already well aware, but even when it is not their intention to do so, humans tend to lead themselves to their destruction. That said, until the time the others are fully prepared, it doesn't matter how much you rack your brains about the sea. It's all but futile.

char_474_glady_CN_003.voiceText: Could you let your operators know to never touch my body or my weapons after combat? It would make me feel bad if anyone complained about any burns.

char_474_glady_CN_004.voiceText: I sound a little too polite...? I'm not yet familiar with the language used on the land. Besides... and this is my only my own opinion, you wouldn't want to see me impolite, would you?

char_474_glady_CN_005.voiceText: As Abyssal Hunters, we must fulfill our responsibilities. To abandon the sacrifices of the past would be an unforgivable act of betrayal. That being said, how many Hunters can I still save other than Specter and Skadi? Even if I save another Hunter who survived, the fear may have crushed them whole long ago. It would only be dragging out their agony.

char_474_glady_CN_006.voiceText: Do you like to sing? What about dancing? How about a dance with me, then? It doesn't matter if you don't know the steps. I will teach you. Songs, art, music... You must never forget these things. These expressions are proof that all those who stand beneath that sky full of stars once lived. That's how they take form and live on. Come, let's dance.

char_474_glady_CN_007.voiceText: Kal'tsit implored me to seek your help, but I don't completely trust you yet. Your technology is primitive compared to Ægir, and your mental state is even more problematic... Many of you are fearful and cowardly. I cannot begin to imagine you people taking on 'that.'

char_474_glady_CN_008.voiceText: The air here is dry. Fighting on land sometimes leaves me feeling dry. This is better than being surrounded by the dead bodies of my comrades, however... when the sea was filled to the brim with shreds of their bodies. Their deaths get etched onto your brain, and the stench of their rotting bodies will fill your mouth each and every time you open it. Even so, we must never hang our heads.

char_474_glady_CN_009.voiceText: We are not of the same race. Do you think we can form an alliance in spite of that? Kal'tsit is far older than me, and I cannot begin to imagine the burden she carries, but they are all things that you must face one day... You need to get stronger. You need to not fear loss. I will watch you by your side.

char_474_glady_CN_011.voiceText: Dr. {@nickname}. I am Gladiia, the officer in charge of Rhodes Island's Ægir affairs. We will have many opportunities to collaborate in the future, but please see me as an outsider. I am not worthy of your trust yet.

char_474_glady_CN_012.voiceText: I see. Your tactics and equipment match your kind's development progress.

char_474_glady_CN_013.voiceText: A new contract? I appreciate your recognition, but I already have many important missions assigned to me. It will be a while until I get to these new missions from you. I apologize for the inconvenience.

char_474_glady_CN_014.voiceText: War. The concept of victory doesn't exist in a war that revolves around the continuance of a race. The only conclusion it can lead to is the destruction of all other races under the night sky. We Abyssal Hunters put our lives on the line to fend off and delay this fate. Always, unrelenting, and without any regrets.

char_474_glady_CN_017.voiceText: As your squadron's aide, I will participate in your trainings.

char_474_glady_CN_018.voiceText: It seems this won't be a difficult battle. Allow me to use this as an opportunity to train your operators' hunting abilities.

char_474_glady_CN_019.voiceText: You are as slow as though you are bogged down in mud, but don't let it get to you. I will slow down and wait.

char_474_glady_CN_020.voiceText: Considering the level of this battle, allow me to save my strength.

char_474_glady_CN_024.voiceText: I'll take care of it right away.

char_474_glady_CN_025.voiceText: Be careful. The currents here will swallow the weak whole.

char_474_glady_CN_026.voiceText: Have you asked for my permission before you tried to run away from me, my dear prey?

char_474_glady_CN_027.voiceText: It won't take even half a second. This lance will pierce your heart.

char_474_glady_CN_029.voiceText: Live. That's the only rule you must follow.

char_474_glady_CN_030.voiceText: An archetypical victory. One day, you will be able to defeat all feeble creatures that come your way.

char_474_glady_CN_031.voiceText: If the preys that got away have no means to share information, then you still have a chance to live.

char_474_glady_CN_033.voiceText: I appreciate the sentiment, but I'm perhaps more comfortable staying in my own little cramped dwelling.

char_474_glady_CN_034.voiceText: Please, respect the land's etiquette, Doctor, or perhaps discourtesy is more your thing?

char_474_glady_CN_036.voiceText: Best be careful. My kind are all monsters in nature.

char_475_akafyu_CN_001.voiceText: What did you need me here for? Hah, that's a huge pile of papers on the desk. Filled to the brim with words, too. Just the sight of them makes me want to cut them in half!

char_475_akafyu_CN_002.voiceText: Hfph—haah! Leave me alone. I'm trying to feel what my new technique is. Aren't techniques meant to be conceived instead of felt, you say? Hmph, I don't need to think. I just need to quiet down and feel it in my heart, and my technique will naturally unfold on my blade when the time comes.

char_475_akafyu_CN_003.voiceText: That ninja... She may be able to stay out of your sight, but she cannot fool my senses. I know not what she's scheming, but I can promise you I shall not engage her right here and now. That said, if I find her trying to do harm to my master—You won't be able to stop my blade.

char_475_akafyu_CN_004.voiceText: Who says I cannot see? Hmph, this medical report is full of shit. If you don't believe me, just try taking me on. Bring as many men as you want, and bring your strongest, swiftest men. Attack me from whichever direction you wish. If you make it anywhere close to my body, I'll accept defeat.

char_475_akafyu_CN_005.voiceText: It hurts my head when I have to listen to those righteous men and their principles, especially the ones that go on and on like they are preaching their scriptures. It doesn't matter what a feast for the ears their words are. They won't hesitate to stab even their family in the back if it benefits them. How is there any righteousness in what they say? They are hypocrites, and my blade will slice them apart!

char_475_akafyu_CN_006.voiceText: I've seen winters like that many times. The snow fell on the ground and turned red in an instant. They were everywhere, either lying prone or still sitting. I could not make out their faces, nor did I want to figure it out. My face and my chest were frozen cold, though my hands, with my blade held tight, felt hotter than ever. Tsk, why am I even telling you all this? You needn't listen, either.

char_475_akafyu_CN_007.voiceText: Hm? How many times have I told you? Don't stand in front of me without a word! What? You wanted to make yourself more clearly seen? You're a strange fellow. I don't need to look at you to tell you apart from others! You think I just let anybody come this close to me?

char_475_akafyu_CN_008.voiceText: {@nickname}, you look just like my master when you have such a serious look on you. I suppose... it's because both you and her are forced to go forward in chase of a grand, ambitious goal.

char_475_akafyu_CN_009.voiceText: My master had me come to Rhodes Island for some peace and quiet, but there is no peace to be had as long as the flames of war rage in my homeland. Nonetheless, as a commander, you have my respect. {@nickname}, I am under your command. Together, we will take to the battlefield, and I shall slay everyone that stands in our way as your blade!

char_475_akafyu_CN_010.voiceText: The air here is nice and cool. Move over a little. Let me lay down a little too.

char_475_akafyu_CN_011.voiceText: Akafuyu, a swordsman, and the strongest you'll find. Taking a fancy to my katana? I will never set my katana down wheresoever I go. Haha, you better keep your distance if you are scared.

char_475_akafyu_CN_012.voiceText: Hey, I'm as strong as it gets already. Stop wasting my time!

char_475_akafyu_CN_013.voiceText: I don't need anyone's acknowledgement, but I appreciate your kindness. I will work to repay the favor.

char_475_akafyu_CN_014.voiceText: Heh... if these guys are still here, they should be dragging me into their celebrations any minute now. How about this, {@nickname}, come with me! We'll drink till we drop tonight!

char_475_akafyu_CN_017.voiceText: Let's get going already. My katana is starting to rust.

char_475_akafyu_CN_018.voiceText: Now we're talking! All of you, come with me!

char_475_akafyu_CN_020.voiceText: No matter who, I shall slay them by my katana!

char_475_akafyu_CN_022.voiceText: I've been waiting to draw my katana.

char_475_akafyu_CN_024.voiceText: Try taking on my blade head on!

char_475_akafyu_CN_026.voiceText: It doesn't matter whether there's one or a thousand of you! I shall slay all that come my way!

char_475_akafyu_CN_027.voiceText: I'll slay even your will to fight back!

char_475_akafyu_CN_028.voiceText: My katana knows exactly where my foes are.

char_475_akafyu_CN_029.voiceText: Where are the foes actually worth fighting?

char_475_akafyu_CN_030.voiceText: That was hardly a battle. I didn't so much as break a sweat.

char_475_akafyu_CN_031.voiceText: We had enemies slip past us? Impossible. There's no way I didn't see them.

char_475_akafyu_CN_032.voiceText: I won't run away. As long as my katana is in one piece, I can still fight!

char_475_akafyu_CN_033.voiceText: What a small room! Don't keep me waiting in here for too long! I might not be able to keep myself from drawing my katana!

char_475_akafyu_CN_034.voiceText: Hmph... Hey, if you were my enemy, I would already have cut you into two halves.

char_475_akafyu_CN_036.voiceText: Now, now! Let's get ourselves all the ale and meat!

char_475_akafyu_CN_042.voiceText: Hey, Doctor, how about some sword training together?

char_426_billro_CN_001.voiceText: You pulled an all-nighter, and you're still not done? Sheesh, what should I do with you...? How much do you have left? I'll help. You should get some rest. Work on your time management next time.

char_426_billro_CN_002.voiceText: I can confirm we've received this shipment of medicine without issues. The quantities are right. As for the payment, could you please let Kal'tsit know I'll take care of that pain-in-the-neck mission for her.

char_426_billro_CN_003.voiceText: Count Hohenlohe, some call him the Hyacinth Count. The way I see it, he's quite a handful with that personality of his. I'm serving as attendant to this Leithanian noble family because of some trouble. What trouble, you ask? Hm... Let's keep this a secret for the time being.

char_426_billro_CN_004.voiceText: That little squirt... Her codename here is uh... Beeswax? Looks like she tripped in the hallway this morning. Can she really cut it? She sure knows how to keep her sister worrying.

char_426_billro_CN_005.voiceText: Rhodes Island provides what the count and I need. In return, I take care of Rhodes Island's troubles in Leithanien. This is what you call a win-win situation, isn't it? Come, shake my hand. This is the beginning of a beautiful friendship, Doctor.

char_426_billro_CN_006.voiceText: The Leithanians' research on Arts has far exceeded my expectations, and their architecture, music, and education... All are worthy of study. One day, I will bring all this back home. Yeah, and I might bring something else along, though.

char_426_billro_CN_007.voiceText: The longer we acclimate to an environment and the different people there, the harder it will get for us to free ourselves, and eventually we'll be made to fit its mold... Don't you agree, Doctor? Well, that's not going to get me tied down here. Not unless I allow it.

char_426_billro_CN_008.voiceText: I'm sure the nobles think of me as an odd thorn in their side. No matter. I don't mind. Though I'd rather keep all this trouble a secret from Beeswax. It's too dangerous... Well, now that I mention it, I can't quite stop worrying about you, either.

char_426_billro_CN_009.voiceText: If it's at all possible, I'd rather stay out of the nobles' bickering. Do you know how much I have to worry about each and every day with all the chaperone work and missions I have? Maybe I should talk the count into letting me hop over here full time. I'm counting on you to help me when the time comes, Doctor.

char_426_billro_CN_010.voiceText: My little sister sometimes talks in her sleep. This one time, I even caught her talking bad about me. Heheh, Doctor, do you know what you said in your sleep the other day?

char_426_billro_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, you must be the Doctor? I'm Carnelian, attendant to Count Hohenlohe... Oh, I'm just a normal operator here at Rhodes Island. Watch what you say around my sister, okay?

char_426_billro_CN_012.voiceText: I see. This is worth studying.

char_426_billro_CN_013.voiceText: There is no need, but I appreciate your sentiment. Thank you.

char_426_billro_CN_014.voiceText: You see, there's a huge number of people and things that I can't stop worrying about, and that number is growing by the day. It's been a while since I was able to do as I please, but since you're up for it... Well, let's put on a show.

char_426_billro_CN_017.voiceText: This is not part of our agreement, but fine. I'm happy to help.

char_426_billro_CN_018.voiceText: Don't worry. I'll bring everyone back.

char_426_billro_CN_020.voiceText: Elegance and etiquette are the way of nobility. Not mine.

char_426_billro_CN_022.voiceText: Between a refined combat style or something more direct, which do you prefer?

char_426_billro_CN_023.voiceText: It's been a long time since my blood boiled like this.

char_426_billro_CN_024.voiceText: Greetings... Let's forgo the bothersome formalities and get this thing started.

char_426_billro_CN_025.voiceText: Gnaw them to shreds and drink their blood!

char_426_billro_CN_026.voiceText: Run them down and beat them to a mash!

char_426_billro_CN_027.voiceText: Careful! Don't let me tear you to shreds so quickly!

char_426_billro_CN_028.voiceText: My oh my, what a pitiful sight. Why are you covered in blood all over?

char_426_billro_CN_029.voiceText: Nothing to worry about then. That was easy enough for you.

char_426_billro_CN_030.voiceText: Okay, that concludes the mission, and right on time, too... Are you hurt, Doctor?

char_426_billro_CN_031.voiceText: Calm down. Just leave the rest to me. They won't get away.

char_426_billro_CN_032.voiceText: Fall back, now! Don't panic. As long as I'm still standing, no one will touch you!

char_426_billro_CN_033.voiceText: Just as I thought. I can relax better in a room without much decoration.

char_426_billro_CN_034.voiceText: Oh... Watch out. My horns could get you.

char_426_billro_CN_036.voiceText: What's wrong? Are you tired? Get some rest. You've worked hard enough already.

char_426_billro_CN_042.voiceText: More work today? Don't spend the whole day sitting, Doctor.

char_478_kirara_CN_001.voiceText: Done with everything. Um... Sorry, do you mind if I read my manga here?

char_478_kirara_CN_002.voiceText: Doing human relationships is so not working out... And all you've gotta do on SNS is send a request and you're friends. Reality is a nightmare.

char_478_kirara_CN_003.voiceText: Utage was my classmate in middle school, and the one who introduced me here. What are we like? Not bad, I guess... but, Doctor, this is what you wanna remember: riajuu are a terrifying species!

char_478_kirara_CN_004.voiceText: Whuh? Why send messages even though we're face to face? I mean... it's 'cause it's easier that way, right, of course...

char_478_kirara_CN_005.voiceText: Back in Higashi, I saw Koga election vans on the street a bunch. I guess their representative was pretty cool... uh, but I don't understand much about that whole side of things, so usually I just voted whatever.

char_478_kirara_CN_006.voiceText: My family says that we all came out of the sea onto dry land forever ago, and that's how we settled down. Huh? Would I wanna go back into the sea? Mmnn... honestly, I could take it or leave it. As long as none of them get Oripathy, all of them are doing pretty fine in Higashi anyway.

char_478_kirara_CN_007.voiceText: World's been kinda messy lately, huh. I hear us and the Kougon guys up north of us are getting heated again. This could suck... I wonder if the new games from them are gonna make it over...

char_478_kirara_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, do you... think my hobbies are weird, or anything? When I was young, all the other kids made fun of me a bunch, like, I was so gloomy, or gross, stuff like that. H-Hmph. Who cares what they said, not like it was anything to care about...

char_478_kirara_CN_009.voiceText: Doctoooor, I'll lend you this game, and this manga and CD too! These are all masterpieces I chose from the heart so once you know them all we'll be soulmates, and then we can have so much to talk about! If you have any other genres you like you can tell me—oh—okay, how about you come over to mine and pick something out?

char_478_kirara_CN_010.voiceText: Oh jeez, gimme a sec here, just a little bit more... just need to land one more hit! —Nice! Rare drop, please and thank you!

char_478_kirara_CN_011.voiceText: ...I'm Kirara. Nice to meet you... Uh, um... So that's all then? Can I leave?

char_478_kirara_CN_012.voiceText: Crap, this goes... uhhhh, but this is kind of a... humiliating name to give a special move, isn't it.

char_478_kirara_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? As in a whole job upgrade...? Ugh, middle management is gonna wear us all out in the end.

char_478_kirara_CN_014.voiceText: I wanted to thank everyone for sticking by me all this way, and... uh, I guess this isn't something you should really do by text, so... um, tha-I mean, it-it's not anything other than that, even! I just wanted to say that!

char_478_kirara_CN_017.voiceText: If you want a supporter, I guess I can help out... I think.

char_478_kirara_CN_018.voiceText: ...Huh? Me? Captain? Me? Are you being serious?

char_478_kirara_CN_020.voiceText: Ah. Yeah, look over there. Enemy came right out of the tall grass.

char_478_kirara_CN_023.voiceText: Oh, crap. I think I'm getting a little nervous.

char_478_kirara_CN_024.voiceText: I've... seriously never seen scenes like this beyond manga before.

char_478_kirara_CN_026.voiceText: This is good, right? Okay, I got it.

char_478_kirara_CN_028.voiceText: Huh? Hey, that move was kind of... kind of pretty cool just now, right?

char_478_kirara_CN_029.voiceText: Hoooooh, holy crap! You're kidding! You can take no-damage runs this far?!

char_478_kirara_CN_031.voiceText: Aaarrnngh, missed, darn. No savescumming in real life. Whatever...

char_478_kirara_CN_032.voiceText: Yeah, this is done for. Let's quit out.

char_478_kirara_CN_033.voiceText: I mean, if it's an option, I'd like to just stay in my room forever...

char_478_kirara_CN_034.voiceText: Whah! Aaaahh, mispress... this one's seriously not happening.

char_478_kirara_CN_036.voiceText: Oh, hey, Doctor. What, hey, you want me to step in to clear an action game or something?

char_478_kirara_CN_042.voiceText: Oh, good stuff on the login bonuses today.

char_369_bena_CN_001.voiceText: Do you think me a princess, sitting elegantly in an office?

char_369_bena_CN_002.voiceText: Don't take Iris's songs as true. They're for the young children, you know. What? Yes, I'm the guards with the scissors—what about it? Chop-chop? That's me making clothes—what did you think it was? *sigh* Adults, honestly. So eager to assume worse.

char_369_bena_CN_003.voiceText: Preservation techniques? I wouldn't know. Even Iris hasn't the faintest clue how I keep things safe, so why would I be telling you?

char_369_bena_CN_004.voiceText: Let me introduce Annie to you. She's my very best friend, and another 'me.'

char_369_bena_CN_005.voiceText: Don't ask me. I don't know why the Castle takes things in from everywhere to keep and then sends them back out. Granny wants me to do it, so I do it. In adult terms, it's work, isn't it? Something someone has to do.

char_369_bena_CN_006.voiceText: Annie's a quiet one by nature, nothing at all like me. C-Controlling her? What are you talking about?! She's a person, she goes where she wants to! She's only by my side because she likes being with me. That's what best friends are like. Aren't they, Annie? 'Mm.'

char_369_bena_CN_007.voiceText: There's too many children here. No wonder Iris doesn't want to leave. Hrmm... if this goes on any longer, we may as well move the whole Castle of Dreams here onto Rhodes Island. It'll save time, and effort.

char_369_bena_CN_008.voiceText: What even is a good girl? Are you saying I'm not good? —Well, I suppose Granny has said there's situations you can't do as you please in, where you need to 'act' a little. Like? Well... 'My greetings to you, I come from the County of Lyndon. My name is Bena.' More or less like that, you know!

char_369_bena_CN_009.voiceText: Granny brought me into the Castle when I was young, and I grew up there. When she retired, I took over her post at the Castle. How am I anything like Iris who just inherits the whole place? What, you think I'm jealous? Not a chance! Iris has to watch out for her figure, and me? I can eat all I want without putting on a pound, ahah!

char_369_bena_CN_010.voiceText: 'Rest soundly. Doctor.' Who cares about that Doctor? Come out and let's go play! 'Alright.'

char_369_bena_CN_011.voiceText: I'm Bena, here to retrieve an idiot who went out and forgot to come home. But I hear there's still things she has to do, and I suppose that's fair. I'll stay and keep her company for a while.

char_369_bena_CN_012.voiceText: You can't show something this violent to Annie and me.

char_369_bena_CN_013.voiceText: Ahah! Well, looks like you know how to work with children after all!

char_369_bena_CN_014.voiceText: Annie, are you ready? We're going to show this eternally hooded hoodlum what our Arts are made of! 'Alright, Bena.'

char_369_bena_CN_017.voiceText: Two people for a single job. This won't be tricky.

char_369_bena_CN_018.voiceText: Annie's got some ideas for you. Listen to me, now, everyone.

char_369_bena_CN_019.voiceText: Let's take it just like a walk in the forest.

char_369_bena_CN_020.voiceText: Interested in pulling these toys apart too?

char_369_bena_CN_027.voiceText: Whatever breaks needs to be fixed.

char_369_bena_CN_028.voiceText: If there's no fixing it, turn it to pieces.

char_369_bena_CN_029.voiceText: What did you expect? I'm a dab hand at doing bad things to bad people!

char_369_bena_CN_030.voiceText: No piece of work who still needs trimming, then?

char_369_bena_CN_031.voiceText: Leave the rest to the adults, then. We're going home.

char_369_bena_CN_033.voiceText: We're two people here! This room's not big enough!

char_369_bena_CN_036.voiceText: Annie's off on an adventure. Want to come along?

char_369_bena_CN_042.voiceText: Hey, no hiding things! What's that you're playing with?

char_469_indigo_CN_001.voiceText: Hm... Huh? Did you say something? W-Why, I'm not ignoring you... I'm just... thinking of something else.

char_469_indigo_CN_002.voiceText: I... I'm not very good at making conversation. I've always been alone. When I first left home to the outside world, I came across many people who were afraid of me. I even got my things stolen. It's no problem, though... As long as I still have my staff, I can work, so I don't often go hungry for long.

char_469_indigo_CN_003.voiceText: Life inside the lighthouse was hardly boring at all. The seas are always changing. However, my teacher drove me out of the lighthouse, and said to me, 'If you don't see more of this world, you won't be able to protect even a small corner of the sea.' That's how I made my way here.

char_469_indigo_CN_004.voiceText: Blue Poison gave me a new pair of gloves. Pretty, aren't they? She said the materials are improved as well. With these, it'll be harder for me to come in contact with any poison even if I hang out with my poison-wielding friends more. Actually, since I've been touching poisons by mistake all the time... it seems I may have built up an immunity.

char_469_indigo_CN_005.voiceText: I used to gaze out at the sea each and every night. No one in town knew what it was we were guarding, and my teacher never told me. All I know is that, where there is darkness, there must always be lighthouses. I will stand firm, with all my power, until that day comes.

char_469_indigo_CN_006.voiceText: Some people say this light is Originium Arts, but according to my teacher, this is a power that originates from my heart. With the light's guidance, those who sail through the foggiest nights will be able to resist the raging tides and find the correct bearing. That is why I will do my best to protect this light.

char_469_indigo_CN_007.voiceText: My tail has a beautiful color? Thank you very much. It's okay. You may touch it. Despite the color, it's not poisonous.

char_469_indigo_CN_008.voiceText: My hair can get tangled up if they get too long. Could you hold it for me? It takes time to get my hair set properly, but it makes it much easier to stay on the move while I'm on the battlefield. I want to be able to help you even more.

char_469_indigo_CN_009.voiceText: I've been starting to think that humans and lighthouses are very much alike... Some people can shine much farther and brighter than even lighthouses. Like you, Doctor. Would it be okay if I stay beside you for a little longer before I go back?

char_469_indigo_CN_010.voiceText: You don't need me to keep watch while you're asleep? Huh? You want me to join you? I-I'll try...

char_469_indigo_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. My name is Aria... Uh, my mistake. It's Indigo. I used to be a lighthouse keeper... apprentice. Now, I'm a Caster... Also an apprentice. Please look after me.

char_469_indigo_CN_012.voiceText: Are these techniques for fending off enemies? My teacher taught me a little, but I didn't know you could do this.

char_469_indigo_CN_013.voiceText: Huh...? A promotion? A lighthouse needs only one keeper. Is that... not the case here?

char_469_indigo_CN_014.voiceText: Eh? I can do much more? It's true. My light is able to shine on a much larger area than before... Thank you. I will keep doing all I can.

char_469_indigo_CN_018.voiceText: Very well... I'll keep this light up. Please be careful not to wander off.

char_469_indigo_CN_020.voiceText: If you won't let us pass through, then we have no choice but to defeat all of you.

char_469_indigo_CN_025.voiceText: These enemies do not compare to the seas' ferocity.

char_469_indigo_CN_026.voiceText: I will stand guard here until daybreak.

char_469_indigo_CN_027.voiceText: It's only for the evil in your heart that you fear the light.

char_469_indigo_CN_028.voiceText: If you want to run away, let me guide you.

char_469_indigo_CN_029.voiceText: Why, if we are so strong, perhaps we don't need to fear the coming of that day.

char_469_indigo_CN_031.voiceText: S-Some enemies got away? I saw. We must let everyone know.

char_469_indigo_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, this way... Don't be afraid. It doesn't matter how dark the path up ahead is, I'll light it for you.

char_469_indigo_CN_033.voiceText: It's okay. I'll be fine by myself.

char_469_indigo_CN_034.voiceText: Oh... Be careful... My hair's all tangled up... It'll hurt if I trip...

char_469_indigo_CN_036.voiceText: You will stay here with me? Why, if there's two of us, the nights won't feel as quiet.

char_469_indigo_CN_042.voiceText: Doctor, would you like me to make the light brighter?

char_485_pallas_CN_001.voiceText: Become an assistant? If the job is similar to that of a priestess of the Hall of the Twelve Heroes, I shall be fine.

char_485_pallas_CN_002.voiceText: Ugh... Ehem, I must not drink, drink so much next time... Ah, Dr. {@nickname}. Why do you sway, so much in your movement today?

char_485_pallas_CN_003.voiceText: The city is a grand sight during the festivals. Theatrical performances, sparkling wine, sports competitions... To be frank, I have even once participated in amateur Formula Chariot racing. That chariot was not cheap. I wonder if its fate was being inherited, or if it was simply abandoned after I left.

char_485_pallas_CN_004.voiceText: To think that there were so many like-minded comrades in Rhodes Island. Yes, poetry! War! Freedom! To gather the people's strength from within the torrent of history, and fight to change this world. How exhilarating! These tragic yet extraordinary stories should be immortalized and passed down forevermore.

char_485_pallas_CN_005.voiceText: After contracting Oripathy, I moved to a small village at the border of Minos. There was a small ongoing war against the Sargon incursions... In the end, the Minoans were victorious. However, rather than the so-called reality, I would rather wish that it spreads slowly as a story.

char_485_pallas_CN_006.voiceText: Simply light the flames of resistance, and it shall burn hot and fierce. Just pass on the story of the 'Goddess of War' to those that dearly wish for liberation! All that I have, is but this infected body of mine, and this unchanging faith.

char_485_pallas_CN_007.voiceText: Is that so. Vulcan, once the champion of weapon forging, is here? This is great news indeed! This weapon in my hand has confounded many a smith, and I have had great difficulty in getting it repaired. Look upon this signature, which belongs to her... Oh? I shouldn't mention it?

char_485_pallas_CN_008.voiceText: The stories of Minoan heroes... There exist both comedies and tragedies alike. However, the noblest part of the Twelve Heroes is that——Without exception, each and every one of them returned to a simple, ordinary life.

char_485_pallas_CN_009.voiceText: To be oppressed for so long that one becomes numb to it is a most pitiable thing. A heart without hope will not burn with the fires of rage. I would never wish for anyone to face cruelty, but those who aspire to become a warrior must possess a bit of hope, a little spark and a timely opportunity.

char_485_pallas_CN_010.voiceText: I am used to thinking while standing upright. From time to time, I am suddenly poked, simply to check if I have fallen asleep on my feet.

char_485_pallas_CN_011.voiceText: I am the Minoan priestess, Pallas. I shall be convalescing at Rhodes Island for a time... Be that as it may, I hope to enjoy my share of alcohol and theatre, and I yearn even more for battle.

char_485_pallas_CN_012.voiceText: To be able to record the acts of the warriors in battle with such realism, what a great convenience it is.

char_485_pallas_CN_013.voiceText: Abandoning glory, the hero decided to return to normal life, but could not, due to Oripathy infection? No... It should not be so...

char_485_pallas_CN_014.voiceText: I am... a believer chasing after the will of the heroes. My weapon shall remain ever sharp and free of rust, to be employed against the forces of injustice and cruelty. My humility shall not be forgotten, and it will remind me of my mission to save others.

char_485_pallas_CN_017.voiceText: Heroes who promise victory, I shall receive your blessings.

char_485_pallas_CN_018.voiceText: I am with you, o great warriors, to fight by your side.

char_485_pallas_CN_019.voiceText: The next time you turn your head, it shall be us returning with victory in hand.

char_485_pallas_CN_020.voiceText: Fear not, for we shall claim victory over these reckless fellows!

char_485_pallas_CN_023.voiceText: There is no room for regret.

char_485_pallas_CN_025.voiceText: O' heroes, for this greatest faith of ours, please stand on our side.

char_485_pallas_CN_026.voiceText: Tremble, in the face of true bravery.

char_485_pallas_CN_027.voiceText: Weep, for that worthless faith of yours.

char_485_pallas_CN_029.voiceText: Have we done it...? I feel only the greatest honor and joy.

char_485_pallas_CN_030.voiceText: Turn about, o heroes. We have achieved a perfect victory, and it is now time to return and enjoy the fruits of our labors.

char_485_pallas_CN_031.voiceText: Listen well, the laments have ceased. This calm heralds the arrival of peace and joy.

char_485_pallas_CN_032.voiceText: Even though the wars of humanity have no end in sight... At this moment, we have protected our dignity. Leave. Keep your heads held high.

char_485_pallas_CN_033.voiceText: My horns are a danger to furniture. I shall be vigilant.

char_485_pallas_CN_034.voiceText: What would you do, should you possess wisdom and strength?

char_485_pallas_CN_036.voiceText: Shall we go and enjoy ourselves at the Minoan-themed multimedia room event?

char_421_crow_CN_002.voiceText: I don't know how my papa is doing nowadays... But, I trust the mayor, so it should be fine.

char_421_crow_CN_003.voiceText: Though Dossoles is noisy and filled with unsavory people, life is still a lot better there than for the Bolívarians outside... Have you not been there yet, Doctor? Let's go together next time then.

char_421_crow_CN_004.voiceText: Phew... Staying indoors all day is so stifling. Doctor, let's head up to the deck to get some fresh air, yeah? I'm sure you must be tired from working for so long.

char_421_crow_CN_005.voiceText: Doctor, do you like the whole fighting and killing business? I'm actually not a fan, but I've seen too much of that stuff, as well as too many people around me doing it. And it kinda rubbed off on me...

char_421_crow_CN_006.voiceText: Getting stronger is a good thing, but there doesn't seem to be anything to do after getting stronger... Doctor, how'd you decide on the things you wanted to do?

char_421_crow_CN_007.voiceText: For the longest time, papa didn't actually want me helping him with work. Given my personality, as you know, I'm not really cut out for it. But, I still gave it my all, because I became his daughter.

char_421_crow_CN_008.voiceText: Hey Doctor, can I scooch over a little closer to you? Um, because the office is so big, it feels a little deserted if I sit this far away. Can I?

char_421_crow_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor, you clearly can't throw a punch, but you're just as reliable as papa. It feels like I can just obey your every word, and not have to think about anything. Huh? For me, that's a good thing.

char_421_crow_CN_010.voiceText: I wonder what's under the Doctor's mask. Lemme sneak a peak...

char_421_crow_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. I'm Rafaela, the one Miss Ch'en introduced, and I'll be formally joining Rhodes Island today. Huh, a code name? Hmm... let's go with La Pluma then.

char_421_crow_CN_012.voiceText: Hmm... Wonder if I can really do this.

char_421_crow_CN_013.voiceText: Doctor, did you need me for something? Oh, a promotion? Hmm... did I do something special?

char_421_crow_CN_014.voiceText: Doctor, I'm stronger now than I was before? Really? I don't feel it... But if you say so, it must be true.

char_421_crow_CN_018.voiceText: I'm pretty good at leading the way.

char_421_crow_CN_019.voiceText: Where are we going this time?

char_421_crow_CN_020.voiceText: Now then, I can't afford to get sidetracked.

char_421_crow_CN_021.voiceText: Woah, Doctor, don't scare me like that.

char_421_crow_CN_024.voiceText: All I have to do is keep them from passing, right?

char_421_crow_CN_027.voiceText: It's a little harder than I expected...

char_421_crow_CN_029.voiceText: Huh, I had no clue I'd even be able to complete a mission like this...

char_421_crow_CN_031.voiceText: Doctor, leave the rest to me. I'll get them.

char_421_crow_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, this way. We need to run.

char_421_crow_CN_033.voiceText: The corridors in Rhodes Island are so wide...

char_421_crow_CN_036.voiceText: Let's go see what Doctor is up to.

char_421_crow_CN_042.voiceText: Ehh... Doctor, when'd you get here?

char_437_mizuki_CN_001.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit told me if you ever chose to place me at your side, it means you've decided to protect me. From the looks of things though, Doctor, I don't think you understand what that means? But I know she must've said it for a reason.

char_437_mizuki_CN_002.voiceText: Fine dining, comics, games, and the people who created them, are all psalms laid out beneath the starry firmament. And my journey is to taste them all— and to eliminate anything that seeks to threaten them.

char_437_mizuki_CN_003.voiceText: Ah, Doctor, you came at just the right time. Quick, come have a taste, I prepared this special sashimi dish using a special technique that best preserves the nutrients and vitality of the ingredients!

char_437_mizuki_CN_004.voiceText: This one, huh? It's a classic arcade game from Higashi, though it's kind of niche now. Want to give it a try, Doctor? Here, you move that yellow mouth around and try to eat as much stuff as you can. But until you've absorbed enough nutrients to become strong, you'll only be prey to others.

char_437_mizuki_CN_005.voiceText: A strong sense of justice? You have the wrong idea, Doctor. I'm personally not that concerned about bad guys, but for various reasons, the people here usually can't do much to them, right? In times like that, if there was some way to make those bad guys disappear... Nobody would lose sleep over that, right? It'd be a breath of fresh air, right?

char_437_mizuki_CN_006.voiceText: Though I don't really understand your rationale, Doctor, what you're basically saying is, only eliminate the people who you've designated as bad guys, right? Because you're a good person, Doctor. What if you were actually a bad guy? Don't say that, that'd be quite troublesome. There's no way I could...

char_437_mizuki_CN_007.voiceText: Sometimes, it feels like there's something on this ship... Familiar, yet also foreign. Gentle, yet also seemingly full of hostility. Doctor, it makes me rather uneasy...

char_437_mizuki_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, what does it feel like to take charge of the lives of so many others with your own hands? If I was in your position, I'd feel very warm, maybe wouldn't even be able to resist trembling... Huh? I was talking about you as a commander, holding on to everyone's lifeline.

char_437_mizuki_CN_009.voiceText: I sometimes think, since the food we eat and the nutrients we absorb become a part of us, if we were to eat the same things and do the same things, would we gradually become the same? Doctor... can we?

char_437_mizuki_CN_010.voiceText: It's time to take a little break, Doctor. Come here, lie down. I'll go grab a blanket.

char_437_mizuki_CN_011.voiceText: Ah, hello there, Doctor. Dr. Kal'tsit tells me you're my commander from today on! It's too bad I don't count as an official operator, but as long as you need my help, I'll do whatever I can.

char_437_mizuki_CN_012.voiceText: I need to absorb and digest all this, right? I'll do my best.

char_437_mizuki_CN_013.voiceText: I got the nod? Does that mean I can go with you to more places and take care of more bad guys?

char_437_mizuki_CN_014.voiceText: On one rainy day, I received an unexpected gift that changed me, but I was not taught how to face the future. Doctor, if it were you, would you have shown me the path yourself?

char_437_mizuki_CN_017.voiceText: It'd be best to not expose myself to others, even my teammates? Mm, I'll do as you say, Doctor.

char_437_mizuki_CN_018.voiceText: I will protect you from the shadows, Doctor, as well as everyone else participating in the operation.

char_437_mizuki_CN_019.voiceText: The deployment plan and secret missions for this operation... Yes, flawless indeed.

char_437_mizuki_CN_020.voiceText: The enemies, huh. They don't look half bad.

char_437_mizuki_CN_023.voiceText: You always help me find my place.

char_437_mizuki_CN_024.voiceText: Weave the tapestry of your tactics boldly and without worry.

char_437_mizuki_CN_027.voiceText: When did you delude yourself into thinking that these tentacles are mere illusions?

char_437_mizuki_CN_028.voiceText: Where there are people, there must be someone to cull the evildoers among them.

char_437_mizuki_CN_029.voiceText: What a tough nut to crack. It'll take some time to digest this battle.

char_437_mizuki_CN_030.voiceText: There are fewer bad guys out there now, and it's all thanks to you, Doctor!

char_437_mizuki_CN_031.voiceText: Hm? Doctor, why'd you let some bad guys through? I'll go clean them up for you.

char_437_mizuki_CN_032.voiceText: If you want to cover everyone as they evacuate, I still have an idea... No, just saving everyone isn't good enough. Only by eliminating all the bad guys here...

char_437_mizuki_CN_033.voiceText: Shall I whip up something tasty to help everyone unwind?

char_437_mizuki_CN_036.voiceText: Achoo! Ugh... Why does it feel like someone's looking right through me...

char_1013_chen2_CN_001.voiceText: You're not the type to sit around the office. It's easier to guard you if I dress more casually.

char_1013_chen2_CN_002.voiceText: I won't doubt Rhodes Island anymore. Your cause, Amiya and Dr. Kal'tsit, and all the other operators here are worthy of my respect.

char_1013_chen2_CN_003.voiceText: The way operators are supposed to see things and deal with problems is nothing I've known before. It'll take some time to get used to this.

char_1013_chen2_CN_004.voiceText: I heard from Amiya what you went through in Siesta. Sounds like you had a tough holiday. What about me? It was terrible. Maybe not terrible. That's all I can say.

char_1013_chen2_CN_005.voiceText: My roots are in Lungmen. That will never change. The world I knew there will stay with me wheresoever I go.

char_1013_chen2_CN_006.voiceText: When I left Lungmen, I thought there was an answer to find, but now I get it. There's no such thing as answers, only actions and results.

char_1013_chen2_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, it's been a while since I left Lungmen and came on board as a Rhodes Island operator. It's about time you treat me as an operator too. It's hard for me to do anything if you are always on your toes around me.

char_1013_chen2_CN_008.voiceText: I've got a lot of people relying on me, and I used to take that trust for granted. It may be harder than ten sets of advanced training every day, but I'll be sure to not betray that trust.

char_1013_chen2_CN_009.voiceText: The events in Chernobog and my experiences in Dossoles both proved one thing—Whether fighting or saving, I must first understand my target. I need to broaden my horizons and open my eyes, Doctor.

char_1013_chen2_CN_010.voiceText: Asleep again... You've done a lot of work already, so I'll let you have ten minutes.

char_1013_chen2_CN_011.voiceText: Ch'en, reporting back in from my holiday in Dossoles. I have a lot of reports to write about my trip, so I'm just passing by to say hello, Doctor. Let me know if you've got something. Now that the holiday's over, everything's back to normal.

char_1013_chen2_CN_012.voiceText: There is always someone out there who's better than us.

char_1013_chen2_CN_013.voiceText: You're giving me a promotion as a Sniper operator? No problem. I'm sure I can set a fine example.

char_1013_chen2_CN_014.voiceText: To tell you the truth, I never thought my shooting would get to this level. I'm more used to fighting with a sword still, but shooting is indeed more convenient in certain scenarios.

char_1013_chen2_CN_018.voiceText: No need to fret. I'll take care of it all.

char_1013_chen2_CN_019.voiceText: Buck up and get ready for battle!

char_1013_chen2_CN_020.voiceText: Are you all ready? Let's go, then!

char_1013_chen2_CN_022.voiceText: Ch'en here. Ready at a moment's notice.

char_1013_chen2_CN_029.voiceText: Pure evil and a little torment is nothing to be afraid of. But there's never anything pure there, that's what's terrifying.

char_1013_chen2_CN_030.voiceText: That was some beautiful teamwork. Great work, everyone.

char_1013_chen2_CN_031.voiceText: Help the wounded, and if you got any strength left, I need a few of you to stand guard with me.

char_1013_chen2_CN_032.voiceText: Stay calm and fall back! I'll bring up the rear!

char_1013_chen2_CN_033.voiceText: Hm? Another new room? Engineering's at it for sure.

char_1013_chen2_CN_034.voiceText: You never learn, do you, Doctor?

char_1013_chen2_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, do you have a field operation next? I'll come with you.

char_486_takila_CN_001.voiceText: Good work, Doctor. Why don't you take a break? Don't worry, I've already finished handling the report... Haha, there's no need to praise me. It's not that I have any extraordinary talents, I've simply become experienced with these things.

char_486_takila_CN_002.voiceText: Wait, wait, Doctor, s-stop tugging, I'll take them out myself! *sigh*... Alright, all the cards I hid up my sleeves are right here. Haha, sure enough, you saw right through me. Next time, if we get a chance to go to Dossoles, I'll show you some even more interesting things.

char_486_takila_CN_003.voiceText: Every time I talk to Miss Ch'en, as well as that Miss Lin, I get all nervous. I don't want to get beaten up again... Huh, you can't tell? No way, Doctor, can't you see my palms are all sweaty?

char_486_takila_CN_004.voiceText: Yo, Doctor, how unusual running into you here. Are you looking for someone? Oh, if it's about Rafaela, I'm afraid I can't help you there. As you can see, without the old man here, we have very little to say to each other.

char_486_takila_CN_005.voiceText: I was thrown into the army reserves by my old man. All of them were pretty much kids, more or less. Some of those people had burning ambitions, but I'd say most had nothing of the sort. Life was tough, so everyone was looking for a way out, nothing more.

char_486_takila_CN_006.voiceText: Dossoles has Miss Candela, so there shouldn't be any issues. It's better that the old man was put behind bars, so he has time to calm down and reflect on his actions. The last time I agreed to help him, I was actually trying to make sense of my thoughts. And that was the last time I asked myself that question... because now, I've found the answer.

char_486_takila_CN_007.voiceText: When we first arrived in Dossoles, Rafaela and I were still very young, and we quickly adapted to life there. Only the old man was still stuck on his old ways, his old ideology... Can't do anything about it, but I figure I should at least try to help.

char_486_takila_CN_008.voiceText: Doctor, here's the mission report from last time. I've already handled the follow-up. Don't worry, there won't be any problems. We've carefully laid out the plans, and if any contingencies pop up to disrupt the situation, I'd be supremely disappointed.

char_486_takila_CN_009.voiceText: So how about it, Doctor? Did you draw the card you were hoping for? Ah, that's too bad. That's a loser... Well, when it comes to gambling, there's nothing less reliable than luck. But rest assured, if you're ever in need of it, I'll be there to deliver it right into your hands.

char_486_takila_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, I'll put all the information I've sorted through over here. Hm? What the... you're asleep. And look at all the important documents you left lying here... You must trust me a whole lot...

char_486_takila_CN_011.voiceText: Hello there, are you the Doctor? Great, you're just as recognizable as Miss Ch'en said you'd be. Right, I should pick out a code name, then? Hmm... Let's go with Tequila! Sounds pretty nice, eh?

char_486_takila_CN_012.voiceText: I'm supposed to imitate this move? Seems painful though.

char_486_takila_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? Huh, already? Thanks a million. In any case, without further ado, let's talk about my work...

char_486_takila_CN_014.voiceText: When Miss Ch'en brought me in, I never thought I'd see a day like this. So, does that mean I'm one of your most capable subordinates? Haha, it's not a joke, whether you need me to be tour guide or something else, you can rest easy knowing you're in good hands.

char_486_takila_CN_017.voiceText: Got it. Leave it to me.

char_486_takila_CN_018.voiceText: I'm in charge of the squad? Haha, I appreciate the trust...

char_486_takila_CN_019.voiceText: Follow my lead. Be careful, and don't fall behind.

char_486_takila_CN_020.voiceText: Come, let us show our guests some hospitality.

char_486_takila_CN_023.voiceText: Sorry, this path is closed for business.

char_486_takila_CN_024.voiceText: I'd like you all to stop right there.

char_486_takila_CN_025.voiceText: Don't get worked up, and say what you need to say.

char_486_takila_CN_026.voiceText: I'm also not keen on using violence to resolve problems.

char_486_takila_CN_029.voiceText: You even managed to account for their sneak attack, Doctor, so there's no shame in them losing like that. I still have much to learn.

char_486_takila_CN_030.voiceText: Everything's taken care of, Doctor. ...How did I take care of it? Doctor, do you really need to hear that?

char_486_takila_CN_031.voiceText: Close one, close one. Are you alright, Doctor? Huh, a few of 'em got away. Let me think...

char_486_takila_CN_032.voiceText: Retreat now! Live to fight another day!

char_486_takila_CN_033.voiceText: So this is the dorm, huh... Mind if I give it a makeover, and buy some little decorations for it?

char_486_takila_CN_034.voiceText: Tsk... Who's tugging on me? ...Oh, it's just you, Doctor.

char_486_takila_CN_036.voiceText: It was raining out there just now, and my hair got a little wet... Ah, excuse me, Doctor, could you grab a towel for me?

char_486_takila_CN_042.voiceText: How are you feeling today? Want to head out for a bit?

char_479_sleach_CN_001.voiceText: File organization is one of my fortes! Uhh... What are these? Data charts and theory analyses...? Seem very complicated, unlike the romance novels I read. Doctor, have you read any Victorian literature? Just between the two of us, I share my name with the protagonist from my favorite work.

char_479_sleach_CN_002.voiceText: I used to believe the Infected would understand if I smiled at them, but now I understand... Before I smile, I should first understand their suffering, and that goes for all those who are oppressed.

char_479_sleach_CN_003.voiceText: Now that I've talked to Amiya and the Doctor, I can understand why she, an elite operator... and the rest of Rhodes Island made that choice.

char_479_sleach_CN_004.voiceText: It's a little embarrassing to say... but I really admire Bagpipe. It doesn't matter what she has been through, she takes pride in the fact she was once a Victorian soldier. Oh, please don't get the wrong idea. I still love Victoria, and it is this love that drove me to leave my homeland.

char_479_sleach_CN_005.voiceText: It wasn't easy to lose the Dublinns. I talked to the girl called Reed afterwards, but it doesn't seem she remembers me. I suppose... that's a good thing for her. Should we get the chance, I would love to have a chat with her about poetry and novels. Oh, and it would be lovely if we became friends.

char_479_sleach_CN_006.voiceText: I have every step of Trooping the Colour memorized by heart, but I still have a long way to go to truly carry the banner's weight and find the way forward.

char_479_sleach_CN_007.voiceText: It takes a little time to care for my hair. I know merely keeping up appearances isn't enough, but I see this as part of living diligently. Doctor, your hair's kind of messy. Would you like me to fix it for you?

char_479_sleach_CN_008.voiceText: If the day comes that you must face those countless fearsome enemies, make sure you stand by my side.

char_479_sleach_CN_009.voiceText: Doctor... if we had met before that incident, I'm sure I would've found myself relying on your help. But I can't well wait forever for someone to tell me what righteousness is. At the very least, on this journey we walk together, I wish to be an ally you can count on.

char_479_sleach_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor, when I see you lounging here, it reminds me of the days I spent lazing around in the Rhodes Island offices... the sunshine, the card games, and everyone... Ahh... It really brings back memories.

char_479_sleach_CN_011.voiceText: You must be Rhodes Island's commander? Operator Saileach, reporting in!

char_479_sleach_CN_012.voiceText: Oh, could you stop for a moment, please? I would like to take notes.

char_479_sleach_CN_013.voiceText: I was... disappointed in them. And so I threw away all the ribbons and medals I'd ever earned. But Rhodes Island is different. Thank you, Doctor. I accept this award.

char_479_sleach_CN_014.voiceText: Even now, the blinding light that fended off the darkness still shines in my dreams, though I am still far, far away from her.

char_479_sleach_CN_017.voiceText: May my banner protect all those who are innocent before my eyes.

char_479_sleach_CN_018.voiceText: My friends, as long as we stand together, there will be no evil we can't overcome!

char_479_sleach_CN_020.voiceText: If battle is unavoidable, I will not allow my weaknesses to go unchecked.

char_479_sleach_CN_023.voiceText: It's my duty to stand here.

char_479_sleach_CN_025.voiceText: Can you hear the children's cries?

char_479_sleach_CN_026.voiceText: Can you feel the cities crumbling away?

char_479_sleach_CN_027.voiceText: Those who plot against you are laughing, and you've never noticed.

char_479_sleach_CN_028.voiceText: Could you ever imagine... those around you would be your friends no longer, and the place you called home would never again be your homeland?

char_479_sleach_CN_029.voiceText: I simply want to defend the people's right to live, and it doesn't matter if they are Victorians or Infected.

char_479_sleach_CN_030.voiceText: You showed me that even weeds struggling to grow in the ruins can stand tall. Thank you.

char_479_sleach_CN_031.voiceText: I can only hope they will come to understand their injustice.

char_479_sleach_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, this time, I'll stay. Hurry and take the others to safety.

char_479_sleach_CN_033.voiceText: Phew... I reckon it won't be easy to slack off once I become an actual staff member here?

char_479_sleach_CN_036.voiceText: Are you tired? I've baked some scones. Please, sit down, have some tea, and tell me what's on your mind.

char_479_sleach_CN_042.voiceText: Hey, Doctor, you look cheerful as always!

char_473_mberry_CN_001.voiceText: Doctor, I'll leave the files I sorted here. Oh, you don't have to thank me. I am used to it, and it's nothing difficult... Um, are you thirsty perhaps? Should I make you some tea?

char_473_mberry_CN_002.voiceText: I'm not very good at speaking any languages other than Yanese. That's why I was a little scared at first and didn't talk much. But everyone's very friendly, and there are a lot of people from Yan here. Phew... it really puts my mind at ease.

char_473_mberry_CN_003.voiceText: Sorry to disturb you, Doctor, but would you happen to know where Provence and everyone else went? My family sent me some goodies from back home, and I thought I'd share some with them since they've been taking care of me... Oh, there are some for you too, Doctor. Please have a taste!

char_473_mberry_CN_004.voiceText: D-Doctor, could you help me look for my little dumpling? It's the small black-and-white doll. I thought I'd left it here, but I can't find it... *Whimpers*, please, I can't sleep at night without it.

char_473_mberry_CN_005.voiceText: The rescue team has to deal with the Catastrophes a lot, so it's only a matter of time for us to become infected. None of us reject anyone because of that. The crystallization on my body isn't very conspicuous, and it doesn't hurt even if you press down on it... Sometimes, I even forget that I have this on my body.

char_473_mberry_CN_006.voiceText: When I first joined the rescue team, I wasn't very used to the climate or the food there. I'd get too homesick to fall asleep at night, and I cried to myself more times many, many times, but whenever I see the people we rescued, I start to think that maybe I can keep at it...

char_473_mberry_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, sorry to bother you... I've been studying Oripathy prevention techniques during Catastrophe relief, and Tsukinogi suggested that I come ask for your advice... Um... Sorry, am I being a bother?

char_473_mberry_CN_008.voiceText: Eep! Doctor, why would you sneak up on me like that? Huh? What am I holding? Oh, this is a letter I got from home. When I made the decision to leave, my parents were so angry that they said they would disown me, but there's a saying where I come from: Blood is thicker than water...

char_473_mberry_CN_009.voiceText: When I got infected with Oripathy, I knew I probably wouldn't be able to live a peaceful life my parents wanted for me. I don't regret it, though... Besides, if I hadn't made my decision, I would never have met you or anyone else from Rhodes Island here and now, hehe.

char_473_mberry_CN_010.voiceText: Doctor? Doctor? S-Sorry to bother you. Please lift your head up a little and sleep with the cushion. If you fall asleep like this, the letters from the report will get all over your face...

char_473_mberry_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm a member of the Yan disaster relief organization 'Chun-qian,' dispatched here as an intern. My name is... Oh, I-I'm sorry. We need to use our codenames here, right? I'm terribly, terribly sorry. Please call me Mulberry.

char_473_mberry_CN_012.voiceText: T-The mountain collapsed, and the ground crumbled...! Looks like special effects from an action movie!

char_473_mberry_CN_013.voiceText: Huh? A promotion? Really? I get a salary from Rhodes Island as well as Chun-qian?! I... I'm so happy...!

char_473_mberry_CN_014.voiceText: This time, I'm not doing this to help someone else, I'm doing it for myself... Doctor, thanks for always being there to cheer me on. Now, I'm sure that everything that I've done is truly meaningful.

char_473_mberry_CN_017.voiceText: I'll do my best to support everyone!

char_473_mberry_CN_018.voiceText: Eh? Me as team captain? A-Are you sure?

char_473_mberry_CN_019.voiceText: Okay, we'll head out right away... Everyone, please stay safe. We'll meet again once this is over.

char_473_mberry_CN_020.voiceText: Watch out, everyone! There's movement up ahead!

char_473_mberry_CN_021.voiceText: Safety goggles... Okay, I have mine on. Let's go!

char_473_mberry_CN_022.voiceText: Phew... Haah! Uh, I'm here! I-I'm not nervous!

char_473_mberry_CN_026.voiceText: I... I can do it too!

char_473_mberry_CN_027.voiceText: Where are you looking? It's dangerous to look around!

char_473_mberry_CN_028.voiceText: It's my job to ensure everyone's safety!

char_473_mberry_CN_029.voiceText: Report! All rescue operations in the area have been completed. Evacuation and escort proceeding without issue! T-Thank goodness nobody's hurt...

char_473_mberry_CN_030.voiceText: Phew, that wraps up the operation. Doctor, was I helpful?

char_473_mberry_CN_031.voiceText: Wait! It's not safe that way... We have to do something. I'll go fetch them right away!

char_473_mberry_CN_032.voiceText: It's not safe here! Everyone, please evacuate! Doctor, follow me!

char_473_mberry_CN_033.voiceText: Whoa, this is the staff dormitory... Um, will I need to pay rent?

char_473_mberry_CN_034.voiceText: Eh? Ah! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

char_473_mberry_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor! I really appreciate it, but please stop trying to sneak any more amulets onto me... I have way too many already!

char_473_mberry_CN_042.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. Do you have work today too?

char_484_robrta_CN_001.voiceText: Hello, Doctor. Have you figured out the style you wanna go with today? Huh...? You didn't call me here for that? I really, really hope you can give it at least a little more thought. Please?

char_484_robrta_CN_002.voiceText: Watch out! I've got tons of stuff in my pocket here. If this negative ion hair softener bumps into the horn growth stimulant and spills... Well... I could end up getting hanged on the deck! It's no joke!

char_484_robrta_CN_003.voiceText: You've probably heard how assassins who know their stuff in anatomy work more efficiently, no? Of course, my goal's not to take anyone's hope to survive away. Instead, I want to turn that hope into something more vivid and brilliant! Styling is an art, but it's also a science!

char_484_robrta_CN_004.voiceText: She looks familiar... Is that the girl who shows up in all those kung fu movies? Whoa, don't ever tell her I'm here! Nah, it's not her that I'm afraid of, but I really don't wanna run into her stylist, Lauder! The last thing I need is anybody calling me 'Bobbi'...

char_484_robrta_CN_005.voiceText: I'm a researcher, not a modeler, and I definitely don't want to be the kind of gal who turns screws on artificial masks under a flashlight day in and day out! Coming on the ship's been kind of like a vacation to me, I guess? If I had to stare at those lifeless faces all day, my brain would get completely fried sooner or later. I'm not doing that no matter how much I get paid.

char_484_robrta_CN_006.voiceText: If I got no money, I couldn't buy any new tools or materials. That's why even I got to work sometimes. Hm... I think the girl who came to me last time just got an academy award? She'd be fine to spot me, right?

char_484_robrta_CN_007.voiceText: Doctor, I asked Dr. Warfarin for some info about your body... and modified my brush texture based around that. I promise you it won't trigger any allergies this time!

char_484_robrta_CN_008.voiceText: If you want to touch my hair, go right ahead. It's pretty messy already anyway. Is that weird? When you do styling work for as many people as I do, you definitely won't find yourself in the mood to work on yourself even if you have the time.

char_484_robrta_CN_009.voiceText: Interesting faces are like stories in their own right. {@nickname}, you are like... a kinda damaged videotape, waiting for someone to dust you off. If the day ever comes that you get repaired, what kind of story will you reveal?

char_484_robrta_CN_010.voiceText: Did you really fall asleep? In that case, I guess I can get to work? Your bone structure, your skin... Whoa, this is even more spectacular than I thought!

char_484_robrta_CN_011.voiceText: Hello, I'm Roberta! We meet again! Once I sign here, I'll be your personal stylist, right? Huh... 'You'll be an operator?' Doesn't matter as long as I get to stay!

char_484_robrta_CN_012.voiceText: Beat up all the annoying guys like this, right? No more difficult than swinging ten brushes around while taking a sip of coffee. I'm from Siracusa, after all.

char_484_robrta_CN_013.voiceText: I've got an entire room full of medals like this one back in my studio in Wrankwood... Hey, Doctor, can't you give me something a little more interesting for my reward?

char_484_robrta_CN_014.voiceText: Since you're giving me another promotion, I want a bigger studio. You'll approve it, right?

char_484_robrta_CN_017.voiceText: Should I go with eyeshadow palette #3001... or perhaps #3002?

char_484_robrta_CN_018.voiceText: Doesn't look like we have a color base that works for all of us...

char_484_robrta_CN_019.voiceText: Let's go, everyone! It's makeup time!

char_484_robrta_CN_020.voiceText: I know exactly which part of the face is the most fragile!

char_484_robrta_CN_021.voiceText: You gotta put on the most suitable style even when you're giving out commands in the frontlines.

char_484_robrta_CN_022.voiceText: These real battlefields give me so much more inspiration than any film set I've been to.

char_484_robrta_CN_023.voiceText: Bring your face closer this way, okay? Thanks. I'll pay attention to how much force I use.

char_484_robrta_CN_024.voiceText: Even the biggest stars out there gotta book me in advance, you know? You should count yourselves lucky!

char_484_robrta_CN_026.voiceText: Infused Originium Slug acid styling spray!

char_484_robrta_CN_027.voiceText: Facial bone full structured self-image shading highlighter!

char_484_robrta_CN_028.voiceText: Wet/Dry ambient color adapted lipstick and blusher!

char_484_robrta_CN_029.voiceText: Whoa... Not even I can replicate that look right now.

char_484_robrta_CN_030.voiceText: What a perfect operation. Makes me want to add a few more touches to bring out that joy on your face.

char_484_robrta_CN_031.voiceText: There's nothing as boring as watching the cowards run. They always stiffen up like Rock Spiders that've spent a bit too much time in antiseptics.

char_484_robrta_CN_032.voiceText: Doctor, need me to give your face a little blush? If you go back like this, the others might worry when they look at you.

char_484_robrta_CN_033.voiceText: Can I do my experiments here? Relax, I won't blow the walls out. At most... I guess the doors and windows might bend a little?

char_484_robrta_CN_034.voiceText: Didn't I say I'm not seeing anyone...? Oh, it's you.

char_484_robrta_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor, can I come over to your room tonight? Your face could really use a massage.

char_484_robrta_CN_042.voiceText: Hey, Doctor, want to try this new look I designed just for you?

char_430_fartth_CN_001.voiceText: It's done. The battle plans, reports, and mission schedules have all been sorted... Eh... Is this not the right way? Sorry, I'm not used to this yet...

char_430_fartth_CN_002.voiceText: Iwona and Ashlock can make quite a ruckus together. I can't hear the wind when they do that. It's a pain.

char_430_fartth_CN_003.voiceText: Hm? Who's that in the training grounds...? The Radiant Knight? Doctor, is it okay if I go check it out up close?

char_430_fartth_CN_004.voiceText: It's really close. When I sit here and look outside, I can see the crops in the distant ripening as the farmers harvest their fields. It's just like my hometown.

char_430_fartth_CN_005.voiceText: It's actually not very hard to become a knight in Kazimierz if you're healthy. All you have to do is sign up at the arena. But to become a real 'knight' is difficult. Real difficult, even for those who are healthy.

char_430_fartth_CN_006.voiceText: I agree with Sona's ideas, and I'm willing to fight for them... Though, I guess I might just be afraid of losing the one place where I belong. Doctor, do you also see Rhodes Island as a place you will protect no matter what it takes?

char_430_fartth_CN_007.voiceText: Thank you for treating us. Sona, Iwona, and Ashlock asked me to bring you these as thanks. And here's one that I picked. It's a small token of my appreciation.

char_430_fartth_CN_008.voiceText: I used to dream of becoming a knight, but on the way to the Grand Knight Territory, I got infected in an accident. I still remember how it felt. The numbness spread from my palm to my fingertips... That was the first time I couldn't hold my sword.

char_430_fartth_CN_009.voiceText: Here's a grass whistle... Want to listen to me use it? I used to whistle with it whenever I had some free time back home. The wind back then is not like it is now. It was clear as crystal, and it wasn't dangerous at all... It was calming.

char_430_fartth_CN_010.voiceText: Finally awake? Here, the files are sorted... Should be right this time.

char_430_fartth_CN_011.voiceText: 'Fartooth' Justyna, Pinus Sylvestris Knightclub. You can call me Fartooth. I've heard about Rhodes Island and you in particular, Doctor.

char_430_fartth_CN_012.voiceText: They're going to lose. If they don't take a proper defense stance, they won't be able to block this one. You've got them.

char_430_fartth_CN_013.voiceText: A promotion? Is that something like advancing to the next round?

char_430_fartth_CN_014.voiceText: There's not much that I want, and I don't have much either. That's why... as long as I'm still standing here, nobody can hope to take anything from me!

char_430_fartth_CN_017.voiceText: ...I'll do as you say. You are my commander, and I'll follow your orders.

char_430_fartth_CN_020.voiceText: Wait, the winds have shifted... Everyone, stay alert!

char_430_fartth_CN_023.voiceText: I hope we can win this match fair and square.

char_430_fartth_CN_024.voiceText: I, 'Fartooth' Justyna, will be your opponent.

char_430_fartth_CN_025.voiceText: The winds are stirring. I can tell.

char_430_fartth_CN_027.voiceText: There's no need to talk in battle.

char_430_fartth_CN_028.voiceText: Let's put an end to this... You can't beat me; accept your defeat.

char_430_fartth_CN_029.voiceText: You've done well, Doctor. This is a glorious victory.

char_430_fartth_CN_030.voiceText: I fended them off just as you instructed... I'm being too solemn? Really...?

char_430_fartth_CN_031.voiceText: I won't attack those who leave the arena.

char_430_fartth_CN_032.voiceText: Go on ahead...! I'll hold them here, Doctor! Lead the others away!

char_430_fartth_CN_033.voiceText: Not bad. The airflow here feels refreshing... Thank you.

char_430_fartth_CN_034.voiceText: Hm? What is it? Want an autograph?

char_430_fartth_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor...? Yeah, I can tell it's you without listening to your footsteps. The winds around you aren't like the others.

char_430_fartth_CN_042.voiceText: Don't move... Your hair's sticking out. That's right. Stay still. I'll fix it for you.

char_431_ashlok_CN_001.voiceText: So, just like the big corporations' office workers, even you have a bunch of deskwork to do. That's quite a lot, too. Do you need any help?

char_431_ashlok_CN_002.voiceText: I never imagined the Radiant Knight would take up employment anywhere. Rhodes Island is a mysterious company.

char_431_ashlok_CN_003.voiceText: Knights may be able to climb back up after they fall, but the Infected don't have such kindhearted options available to them.

char_431_ashlok_CN_004.voiceText: *Cough*... My weapon seems to be acting up, *cough*... Which way is the workshop? That way? Thank you. *Cough*.

char_431_ashlok_CN_005.voiceText: If the knight nobles were able to fulfill their vows and responsibilities, the Infected wouldn't have found themselves so oppressed. But... those nobles... the Kazimierz people would rather sign contracts with those big security companies than trust those knight nobles to protect them from crime and violence.

char_431_ashlok_CN_006.voiceText: They tell me my family met its downfall because I got infected, that I am to blame for everything. Hmph, just what you'd expect from the knight nobles. They're all good-for-nothings who know only to bully the weak.

char_431_ashlok_CN_007.voiceText: Justyna likes to use titles when she talks to me... Why is that? Is the word 'Ashlock' that special to her?

char_431_ashlok_CN_008.voiceText: Sona and I met each other during a team melee match. That was a tough battle, but we reached an understanding and worked with each other as soon as we met. At the very end, she took all my points with her sword, but then apologized to me right away... That's how we started working together.

char_431_ashlok_CN_009.voiceText: If I can't go back home anymore, then all I can do is find the way forward with Sona and the gang. Heh... Becoming an Infected knight hasn't been kind to me, but at least we have the chance to fight. It doesn't matter what miseries the future has in store for us; I'm sure it'll still be a much brighter place.

char_431_ashlok_CN_010.voiceText: Be sure to get enough rest. The break after a match is just as important as your daily training.

char_431_ashlok_CN_011.voiceText: I'm 'Ashlock' Greynuty of Pinus Sylvestris Knightclub. Thank you for taking us in.

char_431_ashlok_CN_012.voiceText: A coordinated assault? Yeah, they work well with each other.

char_431_ashlok_CN_013.voiceText: Is this a medal to prove my qualifications? Oh... Sorry, I still don't have all of Rhodes Island's rules down. Thank you.

char_431_ashlok_CN_014.voiceText: 'When the cannon fire rings through the air, victory is already within sight.'

char_431_ashlok_CN_018.voiceText: You need me to take charge? Okay.

char_431_ashlok_CN_023.voiceText: Battles don't just come to an end.

char_431_ashlok_CN_026.voiceText: Cannon fire is just the first step.

char_431_ashlok_CN_029.voiceText: Wonderful. So this is the art of command. You've opened my eyes.

char_431_ashlok_CN_030.voiceText: Looks like you're good at commanding team battles.

char_431_ashlok_CN_031.voiceText: The more points you lose in the arena, the less likely you are to win.

char_431_ashlok_CN_033.voiceText: Good thing my equipment doesn't take up too much space.

char_431_ashlok_CN_036.voiceText: A present from a fan? It was sent to you? Sorry for the trouble.

char_431_ashlok_CN_042.voiceText: Do we have any missions today?

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_001.voiceText: Hm? Ah, this soil... it can murmur. It can dance. It is my friend.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_002.voiceText: Miss Closure told me I shouldn't walk about Rhodes Island 'fully equipped'... but I'm not used to... revealing... myself. Sorry...

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_003.voiceText: Thank-you letters? Ah, from the Sarkaz workers yesterday? My equipment and type of Arts are a good match for physical work. Besides, their materials and fuel weren't featherweight. And they relied on the power of flesh and blood to ensure Rhodes Island sails smooth... it's incredible.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_004.voiceText: That elite operator... I thought I'd seen enough bizarre Originium Arts in Leithanien to write any wild fantasy. But the moment he pushed apart the fog with a wave of his hand, I understood, as a Sarkaz, he was young yet incredibly ancient.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_005.voiceText: I often think of the soldiers and companions that have left us. Sometimes, I have a sort of delusion that even now, I'm still fleeing... Doctor, have you been to Kazdel before? That was where my journey started, and once, where I'd thought it would end.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_006.voiceText: Dr. Kal'tsit, huh... She startled me, but she's reassuring in spades... One thing, though. Rhodes Island seems to get along well with another mercenary group, too. Could you tell me about them, Doctor? It's best I don't know? I see... then I think I can more or less guess who.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_007.voiceText: I became a Rhodes Island Operator so they could be treated properly, live on properly, and only then would those warriors... have died with meaning. But... since coming to Rhodes Island, I've seen clearly what I, myself, am truly fighting for. That was a first for me.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_008.voiceText: Me, alone, talking to a clay doll...? You're... you're telling you saw me? That was just a kind of ceremony... huh? So everyone already knew? Really? Then I'll be more careful next time, do it late when nobody's up... um, I shouldn't?

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_009.voiceText: From Kazdel to Leithanien, so many marks have been carved onto the suffering. The moment they had no choice but to fight, I realized I had nothing at all. How do you see me, Doctor? You trust me? Will that trust... allow me to live on?

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_010.voiceText: ...The person napping there is the Doctor. Remember that well. Our road together is sure to be long and far.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_011.voiceText: Sarkaz mercenary, Mudrock... You're the Doctor, then. Rhodes Island has saved me many times, and now, I'd like you to let me return the favor.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_012.voiceText: I've had a taste of how Rhodes Island fights before, but, well, this still makes a great reference...

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_013.voiceText: I used to be known as Reunion, and then under the Mudrock Squad, and now... I've been promoted by my former enemy. Is this what they meant by 'life is a rollercoaster?'

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_014.voiceText: Hm? This seems fresh? I never take my helmet off in battle, after all... There's a lot of reasons why, but things have changed now. S... staying like this? If I have to...

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_017.voiceText: I'm simply a Rhodes Island Operator, now. I'll obey your command.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_018.voiceText: The captain... I don't like leading, but... I'm used to it.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_025.voiceText: The land is as my friend.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_029.voiceText: Running is useless... resist it, even if you are not willing to resist. This is the only way I've come to know to face suffering.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_030.voiceText: My friends are whispering their celebration. They cheer our victory, Doctor.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_031.voiceText: Chase them... I'll watch over the battlefield with my friends' eyes.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_032.voiceText: It's not the first I've fled with my back to the enemy. If even more can live on this way... I'll cover your backs.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_033.voiceText: The ceiling's... a little lower than I imagined.

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_034.voiceText: ...Mm? Did you touch me just now?

char_311_mudrok#1_CN_036.voiceText: Doctor? Could you stay with me for a bit? I'd like... to ask you a little about Kazdel. Ah, and my friends have missed you, too.
